1
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:11,380
<i>It's a joyous day for me,</i>

2
00:03:11,577 --> 00:03:14,622
<i>because my autobiography,</i>

3
00:03:14,862 --> 00:03:16,542
<i>is being released.</i>

4
00:03:17,221 --> 00:03:20,541
I'm a very misunderstood man.

5
00:03:21,661 --> 00:03:24,624
If you want to know the real Sanjay Dutt,

6
00:03:24,944 --> 00:03:26,186
read my autobiography.

7
00:03:26,864 --> 00:03:30,144
It's my story,
but written by my buddy, D. N. Tripathi.

8
00:03:30,385 --> 00:03:32,869
And he wishes that I read you a chapter.

9
00:03:36,908 --> 00:03:38,347
"Chapter one...

10
00:03:38,507 --> 00:03:39,949
Bapu and Sanju.

11
00:03:41,153 --> 00:03:43,111
Bapu is Mahatma Gandhi.

12
00:03:43,390 --> 00:03:45,430
And, Sanju... Yours truly, Sanjay Dutt.

13
00:03:45,511 --> 00:03:49,391
Our lives have followed
quite a similar graph."

14
00:03:52,790 --> 00:03:54,230
-Hey, Tripathi...
-Yes.

15
00:03:54,311 --> 00:03:57,275
Killer opening! Moved me to tears.

16
00:03:57,435 --> 00:04:00,234
Your wish is my command.
I've put my soul into it.

17
00:04:00,314 --> 00:04:02,754
Mohammed... Sudama... come here.

18
00:04:03,432 --> 00:04:05,836
Tripathi has written a rump-ripping book.

19
00:04:06,276 --> 00:04:08,797
Read us a chapter. Nanny, take a seat.

20
00:04:10,995 --> 00:04:13,116
The book is titled "Sage Sanju".

21
00:04:13,196 --> 00:04:14,639
"Chapter one...

22
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:16,920
Bapu and Sanju.

23
00:04:17,639 --> 00:04:19,558
Bapu is Mahatma Gandhi.

24
00:04:19,759 --> 00:04:21,838
And, Sanju... Yours truly, Sanjay Dutt.

25
00:04:22,683 --> 00:04:25,441
Our lives have followed
quite a similar graph.

26
00:04:25,562 --> 00:04:28,962
For instance, we've both spent
a lot of time in prison.

27
00:04:29,882 --> 00:04:31,484
He's a national hero.

28
00:04:32,124 --> 00:04:34,124
I'm a Bollywood hero.

29
00:04:34,723 --> 00:04:36,043
He was against violence.

30
00:04:36,122 --> 00:04:39,888
He walked with a stick
but never used it as a weapon

31
00:04:40,125 --> 00:04:44,366
I had an AK-56 rifle
and never used it either.

32
00:04:45,046 --> 00:04:46,684
He dreamed of a free India.

33
00:04:47,046 --> 00:04:50,410
I dream of... my freedom."

34
00:04:50,888 --> 00:04:53,086
Maanyata, it's a slow starter.

35
00:04:53,568 --> 00:04:56,486
Don't worry, the story picks up later.

36
00:05:02,931 --> 00:05:04,008
Hold this...

37
00:05:04,650 --> 00:05:06,494
pick up the bell... ring it.

38
00:05:07,136 --> 00:05:09,494
Go around and worship me.

39
00:05:09,573 --> 00:05:13,571
You've elevated me to Mahatma Gandhi
in the first chapter.

40
00:05:13,650 --> 00:05:15,615
By the end, you'll turn me into god!

41
00:05:15,737 --> 00:05:18,708
Find a temple for sale.

42
00:05:18,852 --> 00:05:20,735
He'll put me on the altar.

43
00:05:20,814 --> 00:05:22,134
Sorry, Tripathi.

44
00:05:23,417 --> 00:05:25,336
Buddy, tell me...

45
00:05:26,298 --> 00:05:29,057
are shoes allowed inside a temple?

46
00:05:30,298 --> 00:05:31,504
Not at all, Sanju.

47
00:05:31,583 --> 00:05:34,219
Then how dare you wear shoes
in front of God?

48
00:05:37,940 --> 00:05:41,062
Sanju, I'd told you, I'm no biographer.

49
00:05:41,142 --> 00:05:42,781
I'm a songwriter...

50
00:05:44,022 --> 00:05:45,541
Sanju... please!

51
00:05:52,545 --> 00:05:55,063
What about me reminds you of Gandhi?

52
00:05:55,621 --> 00:05:56,823
I'll write another draft.

53
00:05:57,907 --> 00:06:00,427
<i>Shithead, you jacked my book!</i>

54
00:06:01,025 --> 00:06:04,144
<i>Our correspondent is outside</i>
<i>the Supreme Court.</i>

55
00:06:04,588 --> 00:06:08,151
<i>In moments, we'll know</i>
<i>whether the actor, Sanjay Dutt,</i>

56
00:06:08,230 --> 00:06:10,363
<i>will go to prison or be free.</i>

57
00:06:10,588 --> 00:06:14,990
<i>In 2006, the Anti-Terrorism Court</i>
<i>had sentenced Sanjay Dutt</i>

58
00:06:15,071 --> 00:06:18,111
<i>to six years imprisonment</i>
<i>in the Mumbai bomb blast case.</i>

59
00:06:18,512 --> 00:06:21,832
<i>He'd appealed to the Supreme Court</i>
<i>against the judgment.</i>

60
00:06:22,032 --> 00:06:26,235
<i>The judgment was expected next week.</i>

61
00:06:26,394 --> 00:06:28,632
<i>But we've just received information</i>

62
00:06:28,711 --> 00:06:31,553
<i>the Supreme Court</i>
<i>will give its verdict today.</i>

63
00:06:32,034 --> 00:06:35,396
<i>Stay tuned, as we report live</i>
<i>from the Supreme Court.</i>

64
00:06:35,798 --> 00:06:37,996
<i>Dinesh, give us an update.</i>

65
00:06:38,075 --> 00:06:41,758
<i>The verdict is out.</i>
<i>Sanjay Dutt will go to prison.</i>

66
00:06:41,838 --> 00:06:44,481
<i>The Court has sentenced him to five years,</i>

67
00:06:44,603 --> 00:06:47,236
<i>for possession of an AK-56 rifle.</i>

68
00:06:47,314 --> 00:06:50,160
<i>When does he go to prison?</i>

69
00:06:50,280 --> 00:06:53,083
<i>The Court has given him</i>
<i>a month to surrender</i>

70
00:06:53,164 --> 00:06:57,240
<i>so he can complete his films.</i>

71
00:06:57,360 --> 00:07:00,201
<i>His father, late Sunil Dutt,</i>
<i>popular actor and politician...</i>

72
00:07:00,603 --> 00:07:04,601
<i>his mother, late Nargis,</i>
<i>iconic actor of the '60s...</i>

73
00:07:04,681 --> 00:07:08,127
<i>the scion of this eminent family,</i>
<i>Sanjay, will go to prison.</i>

74
00:07:08,607 --> 00:07:10,886
<i>Let's hear what people have to say.</i>

75
00:07:11,403 --> 00:07:14,809
<i>Five years is nothing.</i>
<i>He should be hanged!</i>

76
00:07:14,931 --> 00:07:17,208
<i>Traitor... a bloody terrorist!</i>

77
00:07:17,286 --> 00:07:19,413
<i>Celebrities have it easy.</i>

78
00:07:19,765 --> 00:07:21,885
<i>Such terrorists should be shot dead!</i>

79
00:07:34,891 --> 00:07:36,654
Come inside.

80
00:07:48,373 --> 00:07:51,179
<i>When the kids start school,</i>

81
00:07:51,736 --> 00:07:54,055
<i>they are sure to be asked...</i>

82
00:07:54,695 --> 00:07:58,978
<i>"Where's your terrorist-dad? In prison?"</i>

83
00:07:59,580 --> 00:08:03,696
<i>It'll be easier for them to say,</i>
<i>"No, he's dead."</i>

84
00:08:18,384 --> 00:08:19,672
<i>Sanju!</i>

85
00:08:20,061 --> 00:08:22,903
Suicide may solve your problem,

86
00:08:23,023 --> 00:08:24,186
not your kids'.

87
00:08:26,505 --> 00:08:28,665
They'll still be called terrorist's kids.

88
00:08:33,950 --> 00:08:36,988
We decided to fight, didn't we?

89
00:08:37,666 --> 00:08:40,748
-That we'll get the truth out there.
-Didn't we try?

90
00:08:41,350 --> 00:08:43,991
What did we get? Bapu and Sanju!

91
00:08:44,070 --> 00:08:46,909
That's what you get with knuckleheads.

92
00:08:46,988 --> 00:08:48,068
Write it yourself.

93
00:08:48,148 --> 00:08:50,952
Struggled with a four-line suicide note.

94
00:08:51,034 --> 00:08:52,832
Imagine a 400-page book!

95
00:08:52,953 --> 00:08:54,246
We'll find a good writer.

96
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:56,590
Why will they be interested?

97
00:08:56,671 --> 00:08:59,595
It's said,
"Bad choices make good stories."

98
00:09:00,834 --> 00:09:03,432
And you're the king of bad choices.

99
00:09:04,433 --> 00:09:06,634
Some writer out there
will understand this.

100
00:09:20,361 --> 00:09:22,038
Sanju, be respectful.

101
00:09:22,117 --> 00:09:24,164
<i>She's no Tripathi. She's Winnie Diaz.</i>

102
00:09:24,602 --> 00:09:26,044
<i>World's top biographer.</i>

103
00:09:26,882 --> 00:09:28,127
<i>She's down from London.</i>

104
00:09:28,212 --> 00:09:31,040
Control slang like...
rump-ripper, jacked...

105
00:09:31,722 --> 00:09:32,686
Got it.

106
00:09:46,325 --> 00:09:47,166
Winnie

107
00:09:47,846 --> 00:09:49,811
I won't take much of your time.

108
00:09:49,933 --> 00:09:53,089
-I wanted--
-I can't write your biography. I'm sorry.

109
00:09:53,810 --> 00:09:54,616
Why not?

110
00:09:57,888 --> 00:10:01,211
...I asked around and...

111
00:10:02,171 --> 00:10:04,810
And they said I'm a terrorist.

112
00:10:10,414 --> 00:10:13,012
Who are these people? Do they know me?

113
00:10:13,212 --> 00:10:16,536
Do they hang out with me?

114
00:10:16,976 --> 00:10:18,896
Then how can they be so sure?

115
00:10:19,458 --> 00:10:23,454
Their opinion is based
merely on TV and print news.

116
00:10:23,814 --> 00:10:26,619
And these TV anchors, newspaper reporters,

117
00:10:26,699 --> 00:10:28,630
who dish out opinions every day,

118
00:10:28,713 --> 00:10:30,656
haven't met me either!

119
00:10:31,178 --> 00:10:34,422
The media has maligned me.

120
00:10:35,023 --> 00:10:38,538
So, I need a good writer
to present my side of the story.

121
00:10:38,617 --> 00:10:44,064
You think millions
will read your biography?

122
00:10:44,502 --> 00:10:46,311
It doesn't work like that.

123
00:10:46,465 --> 00:10:50,864
Thousands of books
rot away in book stores.

124
00:10:51,266 --> 00:10:53,465
Once in a blue moon a book comes that--

125
00:10:53,546 --> 00:10:55,901
That's a rump-ripper!

126
00:10:56,063 --> 00:10:58,911
My story's that!

127
00:10:59,111 --> 00:11:00,749
What's there in your life story?

128
00:11:04,346 --> 00:11:08,149
Give me just one hour.
Guns, drugs, alcohol...

129
00:11:08,309 --> 00:11:10,829
Pick any chapter, I'll tell you the story.

130
00:11:11,069 --> 00:11:13,268
I guarantee, you'll be jacked...

131
00:11:14,108 --> 00:11:18,751
I mean... jack... it'll be a J K Rowling.

132
00:11:20,117 --> 00:11:22,070
I have a month to surrender.

133
00:11:23,630 --> 00:11:26,394
This time I may not survive.

134
00:11:27,233 --> 00:11:28,355
One hour, please.

135
00:11:34,597 --> 00:11:37,199
5 p.m. tomorrow. Right here.

136
00:11:38,714 --> 00:11:42,320
At 6 p.m., I'll tell you
if I'm jacked or not.

137
00:11:56,559 --> 00:11:59,882
From Amitabh Bachchan to Sachin Tendulkar

138
00:12:00,002 --> 00:12:01,803
you've upset everyone.

139
00:12:03,127 --> 00:12:07,968
So many heroes, but you'll pen
a terrorist's biography!

140
00:12:10,725 --> 00:12:11,974
This is fake news.

141
00:12:13,322 --> 00:12:17,449
He too is a fake.
This is a pressure tactic.

142
00:12:17,529 --> 00:12:19,127
-Who are you?
-Zubin Mistry.

143
00:12:20,617 --> 00:12:22,125
I construct malls.

144
00:12:22,607 --> 00:12:25,371
I suggest you don't write this book.

145
00:12:28,052 --> 00:12:30,688
<i>And you came all the way to suggest it?</i>

146
00:12:30,889 --> 00:12:35,136
I'm here daily to jog. Saw you here, so...

147
00:12:35,295 --> 00:12:38,338
Jog in a suit? Is work-wear shorts?

148
00:12:42,379 --> 00:12:43,737
He hit me.

149
00:12:43,817 --> 00:12:46,338
He's on cocaine, LSD, heroin...

150
00:12:47,732 --> 00:12:51,859
A womanizer, too. Ask him his score.

151
00:12:51,979 --> 00:12:54,897
Any number less than 200, he's lying.

152
00:12:54,981 --> 00:12:58,736
Want to know his truth? Call me.

153
00:13:09,903 --> 00:13:11,423
Sanju.

154
00:13:16,021 --> 00:13:18,786
For once, I feel like thanking the press.

155
00:13:18,906 --> 00:13:21,545
One headline, and you're here.

156
00:13:22,184 --> 00:13:25,310
-Why did you get this printed?
-I didn't, Winnie.

157
00:13:25,708 --> 00:13:28,825
Reporters live outside my gate.
They follow me everywhere.

158
00:13:28,905 --> 00:13:30,423
If you were a doctor,

159
00:13:30,504 --> 00:13:33,425
they'd print, "Sanju ill",
an actress... "Sanju's new lady."

160
00:13:33,505 --> 00:13:36,230
They want spicy headlines. Not the truth.

161
00:13:36,309 --> 00:13:38,790
-That's why we've come to you.
-Will he tell me the truth?

162
00:13:39,227 --> 00:13:41,868
Nothing but the truth. Fire away.

163
00:13:44,951 --> 00:13:47,708
Excluding your wife,
how many women have you slept with?

164
00:13:49,230 --> 00:13:50,269
Look here.

165
00:13:56,231 --> 00:13:59,073
Should I count the prostitutes or...

166
00:13:59,193 --> 00:14:01,036
No, let's keep them aside.

167
00:14:01,678 --> 00:14:04,753
Never kept a score-card.

168
00:14:05,353 --> 00:14:10,440
But once, I did the math,
I recalled around 308.

169
00:14:10,519 --> 00:14:14,878
I must've missed a few.
On the safe side, let's say... 350.

170
00:14:22,239 --> 00:14:23,559
Do you know him?

171
00:14:25,766 --> 00:14:28,203
Zubin! He was my friend.

172
00:14:28,924 --> 00:14:30,680
I nicknamed him "God".

173
00:14:30,761 --> 00:14:33,762
Since you picked him,
let's start with chapter "God".

174
00:14:39,963 --> 00:14:43,809
1981... my debut film.
He was always on the sets.

175
00:14:43,889 --> 00:14:47,378
Dad was directing me
and I was nervous as hell.

176
00:14:47,688 --> 00:14:50,764
<i>Is this love?</i>

177
00:14:52,248 --> 00:14:54,652
<i>Yes, my dove!</i>

178
00:14:55,530 --> 00:14:56,768
Cut...

179
00:14:56,888 --> 00:15:00,177
Sonny, your lips are off sync.

180
00:15:00,255 --> 00:15:03,294
Match them to the song.

181
00:15:04,298 --> 00:15:09,454
And... a romantic reaction
when the girl sings.

182
00:15:09,535 --> 00:15:11,494
But, Dad, where's the girl?

183
00:15:11,577 --> 00:15:13,812
How do I react to a cold camera?

184
00:15:13,892 --> 00:15:17,340
An actor's job is to imagine.

185
00:15:17,540 --> 00:15:22,695
Imagine a beautiful actress
in front of you.

186
00:15:22,775 --> 00:15:25,215
Ganpat, come here. Observe.

187
00:15:32,177 --> 00:15:35,381
<i>Is this love?</i>

188
00:15:36,861 --> 00:15:39,151
<i>Yes, my dove!</i>

189
00:15:41,260 --> 00:15:46,265
<i>In your absence</i>
<i>Day and night eclipse</i>

190
00:15:46,344 --> 00:15:49,982
<i>And an hour is forever</i>

191
00:15:50,301 --> 00:15:53,386
<i>Is this love?</i>

192
00:15:54,825 --> 00:15:57,104
<i>Yes, my dove!</i>

193
00:15:58,626 --> 00:15:59,784
Cut.

194
00:16:01,349 --> 00:16:03,947
Come. Give it a go.

195
00:16:04,349 --> 00:16:06,427
Let's give him a heroine.

196
00:16:07,066 --> 00:16:09,073
Ganpat, come here.

197
00:16:09,792 --> 00:16:12,831
Hold this and stand here.

198
00:16:13,157 --> 00:16:15,028
-Don't move.
-Good idea.

199
00:16:18,513 --> 00:16:21,513
<i>Is this love?</i>

200
00:16:23,110 --> 00:16:25,231
<i>Yes, my dove!</i>

201
00:16:27,397 --> 00:16:32,073
<i>In your absence</i>
<i>Day and night eclipse</i>

202
00:16:32,633 --> 00:16:35,598
<i>And an hour is forever</i>

203
00:16:36,478 --> 00:16:38,757
<i>Is this love?</i>

204
00:16:38,838 --> 00:16:40,195
<i>Yes!</i>

205
00:16:41,036 --> 00:16:43,116
<i>Yes, my dove!</i>

206
00:16:43,919 --> 00:16:44,721
Cut it!

207
00:16:45,241 --> 00:16:48,838
Well played, Ramu. Ace!

208
00:16:49,759 --> 00:16:51,557
Sonny...

209
00:16:54,402 --> 00:16:57,359
-You've been smoking?
-No, Dad.

210
00:17:00,604 --> 00:17:01,725
Now you lie, too?

211
00:17:03,124 --> 00:17:07,762
Thousands struggle to be an actor...
with no luck.

212
00:17:07,841 --> 00:17:12,567
You've got it on a silver platter,
respect that.

213
00:17:13,207 --> 00:17:16,684
Drinking, smoking...
will show on your face.

214
00:17:16,766 --> 00:17:18,849
The camera spares no one.

215
00:17:20,769 --> 00:17:24,007
Quit smoking or I'll shelve the film.

216
00:17:38,335 --> 00:17:43,738
Smoke with your left hand.
Fathers sniff the right hand.

217
00:17:54,060 --> 00:17:57,859
Bro, I'm the first actor in the world
to romance a bandit.

218
00:17:57,976 --> 00:17:59,977
But, dad praised the cameraman.

219
00:18:00,056 --> 00:18:01,942
"Well played, Ramu! Ace!"

220
00:18:02,102 --> 00:18:05,152
However well I do, he never praises me.

221
00:18:05,753 --> 00:18:08,261
He insults me publicly.

222
00:18:08,340 --> 00:18:13,389
-Reason with him.
-That would be suicide.

223
00:18:14,550 --> 00:18:16,903
You're too scared of your dad.

224
00:18:17,141 --> 00:18:19,146
Hey, try this.

225
00:18:20,546 --> 00:18:22,233
It bumps up confidence.

226
00:18:22,315 --> 00:18:26,507
Gladiators would take this before a fight.

227
00:18:32,230 --> 00:18:33,467
Watch.

228
00:18:34,028 --> 00:18:38,793
Put this in your nose... and snort it all.

229
00:18:38,993 --> 00:18:42,908
I make my Pomeranian snort it
and he thinks he's an Alsatian.

230
00:18:43,672 --> 00:18:44,831
Try it.

231
00:18:47,275 --> 00:18:49,791
Hey! I've been taking it for years.

232
00:18:50,392 --> 00:18:53,197
I'm stronger than you. Try me.

233
00:19:09,842 --> 00:19:11,239
<i>O light of my soul!</i>

234
00:19:13,081 --> 00:19:17,916
<i>If you're heaven's king, I'm your queen</i>

235
00:19:19,601 --> 00:19:23,845
<i>If you're the needle, I'm the thread</i>

236
00:19:25,841 --> 00:19:30,285
<i>Then why our union</i>

237
00:19:30,930 --> 00:19:35,082
<i>So half-baked, half-baked?</i>

238
00:19:36,369 --> 00:19:39,855
Dad thinks that I can't lip sync to songs.

239
00:19:59,049 --> 00:20:01,655
<i>I'm a fine catch, so are you</i>

240
00:20:01,855 --> 00:20:04,456
<i>Marry me, my love</i>

241
00:20:04,815 --> 00:20:09,531
<i>Let sparks fly</i>
<i>So fine, so bright</i>

242
00:20:21,621 --> 00:20:24,220
<i>I'm a fine catch, so are you</i>

243
00:20:24,414 --> 00:20:27,018
<i>But, I'm a free bird</i>

244
00:20:27,382 --> 00:20:32,151
<i>Keep your fireworks</i>
<i>Too fine, too bright</i>

245
00:20:32,230 --> 00:20:34,819
<i>Take my hand</i>
<i>Marry me quick</i>

246
00:20:34,937 --> 00:20:37,783
<i>Make me yours in a click</i>

247
00:20:37,982 --> 00:20:40,354
<i>Listen up, I'm a wild stallion</i>

248
00:20:40,476 --> 00:20:43,540
<i>Why reduce me to a mere medallion?</i>

249
00:20:45,463 --> 00:20:48,067
<i>I'm a fine catch, so are you</i>

250
00:20:48,266 --> 00:20:50,863
<i>Marry me, my love</i>

251
00:20:51,183 --> 00:20:54,869
<i>Let sparks fly</i>
<i>So fine, so bright</i>

252
00:20:55,387 --> 00:20:56,429
<i>No way, love!</i>

253
00:20:56,509 --> 00:20:59,184
<i>I'm a fine catch, so are you</i>

254
00:20:59,264 --> 00:21:01,829
<i>But, I'm a free bird</i>

255
00:21:02,310 --> 00:21:07,227
<i>Keep your fireworks</i>
<i>Too fine, too bright</i>

256
00:21:11,152 --> 00:21:14,719
<i>That night, one more Pomeranian</i>
<i>turned into an Alsatian.</i>

257
00:21:14,802 --> 00:21:16,831
<i>God's powder was magic.</i>

258
00:21:16,909 --> 00:21:19,316
<i>My confidence was sky-rocketing.</i>

259
00:21:22,074 --> 00:21:24,235
-Where's the bottle?
-Your dad chucked it.

260
00:21:25,833 --> 00:21:29,475
Damn! For how long will he control me?

261
00:21:30,358 --> 00:21:33,234
My father controlled me for 60 years.

262
00:21:33,794 --> 00:21:35,754
-How did he let go?
-He popped it.

263
00:21:38,718 --> 00:21:40,929
Dudes, don't leave. The vodka's coming.

264
00:21:41,008 --> 00:21:43,117
The bar's closed, Sanju.

265
00:21:43,196 --> 00:21:46,800
Dad thinks cutting supply
will make us quit?

266
00:21:47,120 --> 00:21:48,882
I have a back-up daddy

267
00:21:49,007 --> 00:21:51,078
who'll fill up our mugs.

268
00:21:51,159 --> 00:21:53,765
-Back-up dad?
-My girlfriend's pop.

269
00:22:07,327 --> 00:22:08,525
Is daddy home?

270
00:22:09,044 --> 00:22:11,410
Yes, don't sneak in through the balcony.

271
00:22:11,968 --> 00:22:14,211
I'll ring the doorbell. Wake him.

272
00:22:16,247 --> 00:22:17,447
At this hour?

273
00:22:18,766 --> 00:22:20,091
What's so important?

274
00:22:21,369 --> 00:22:23,090
I want something, baby.

275
00:22:27,851 --> 00:22:30,533
I'll be there in five. Open the door.

276
00:22:39,214 --> 00:22:40,535
Wake up your dad.

277
00:22:45,739 --> 00:22:50,106
Dad, mom... wake up. Sanju's here.

278
00:22:50,184 --> 00:22:52,295
At 1 a.m.? Is everything okay?

279
00:22:52,376 --> 00:22:54,460
Took him six months to muster courage.

280
00:22:54,540 --> 00:22:57,100
He'd said, once his career kick started,

281
00:22:57,221 --> 00:22:59,616
he'll ask for my hand.

282
00:22:59,698 --> 00:23:02,462
Just the hand, or all of you?

283
00:23:06,023 --> 00:23:07,899
We'll ask for the 18-year-old scotch.

284
00:23:08,097 --> 00:23:09,459
Will the old fart agree?

285
00:23:09,579 --> 00:23:12,381
If he doesn't agree, we grab and flee!

286
00:23:14,505 --> 00:23:16,503
Hello, child. How are you?

287
00:23:16,820 --> 00:23:20,546
Before you ask for anything,
I have something for you.

288
00:23:25,382 --> 00:23:26,184
Ten rupees?

289
00:23:26,744 --> 00:23:29,467
My father's gift to me
when I joined the Navy.

290
00:23:29,548 --> 00:23:32,842
He said, "There are two kinds of bills."

291
00:23:33,158 --> 00:23:35,508
"Real and fake."

292
00:23:35,746 --> 00:23:38,431
When you tug at a real bill...

293
00:23:40,592 --> 00:23:41,680
it won't tear.

294
00:23:42,625 --> 00:23:44,867
You're starting your career.

295
00:23:44,947 --> 00:23:48,032
Life will pull you left and right.

296
00:23:48,113 --> 00:23:53,270
But if you stay honest,
nothing can rip you apart.

297
00:23:54,836 --> 00:23:57,834
My father's wisdom is now yours.

298
00:23:58,362 --> 00:23:59,831
Homi, let him sit.

299
00:23:59,911 --> 00:24:01,514
Sit.

300
00:24:02,432 --> 00:24:03,918
Now tell us.

301
00:24:04,155 --> 00:24:05,959
What brings you here?

302
00:24:08,118 --> 00:24:12,798
The real reason we're here is...
we have the midnight urge.

303
00:24:15,280 --> 00:24:16,603
Can't control it anymore.

304
00:24:21,922 --> 00:24:25,164
Look, we're weak with idioms.

305
00:24:25,838 --> 00:24:28,645
Tell us clearly, what's a "midnight urge"?

306
00:24:28,725 --> 00:24:30,483
Midnight urge means...

307
00:24:37,006 --> 00:24:39,327
I'm 21 now. It's a biological need.

308
00:24:39,487 --> 00:24:43,044
As soon as midnight strikes...
the urge surges.

309
00:24:43,485 --> 00:24:47,287
I need it now... or I'm gonna explode!

310
00:24:48,210 --> 00:24:50,419
But dad doesn't allow it.

311
00:24:50,658 --> 00:24:53,567
He's orthodox. So I sin in secret.

312
00:24:54,250 --> 00:24:57,652
Once, I was enjoying an 18-year-old
on the terrace... dad walked in.

313
00:24:57,733 --> 00:25:01,329
I told him frankly, "Dad, I'm an adult.

314
00:25:01,410 --> 00:25:04,492
My friends do it every night.
Their parents never object."

315
00:25:04,734 --> 00:25:08,850
He said, "Alright, have your 18-year-old.
But don't hide.

316
00:25:08,931 --> 00:25:11,575
Do it openly on the dining table,
before the family.

317
00:25:11,654 --> 00:25:13,976
And that too, only once a month."

318
00:25:14,056 --> 00:25:16,702
Daddy, how will once a month
quench this thirst?

319
00:25:17,213 --> 00:25:19,055
Now I frequent the illicit joints.

320
00:25:19,133 --> 00:25:21,615
16, 18, 21...
I grab whatever is available.

321
00:25:22,097 --> 00:25:27,016
I park on a lonely stretch,
and indulge in the backseat.

322
00:25:27,096 --> 00:25:28,699
Only fear is the cops.

323
00:25:29,183 --> 00:25:31,420
They peek when you're about to peak.

324
00:25:31,700 --> 00:25:33,986
Ma'am, try the backseat.

325
00:25:36,699 --> 00:25:39,104
You were a Navy Captain.

326
00:25:39,183 --> 00:25:42,312
You must've tasted the best
on every shore.

327
00:25:43,862 --> 00:25:48,384
Be kind, let us taste some from your home.

328
00:25:50,677 --> 00:25:52,824
-May we get one each?
-What!

329
00:25:53,223 --> 00:25:54,466
Okay, we'll share one.

330
00:25:56,587 --> 00:25:59,238
When daddy gets the urge,
you happily serve.

331
00:25:59,517 --> 00:26:03,108
All we get is a "How dare you!"
Sorry, I've promised my friend.

332
00:26:03,188 --> 00:26:06,150
I'm gonna grab one.

333
00:26:06,270 --> 00:26:08,398
Stop!

334
00:26:11,186 --> 00:26:12,154
Soda or water?

335
00:26:17,667 --> 00:26:19,391
And return my papa's box.

336
00:26:23,156 --> 00:26:24,515
Can I say something?

337
00:26:25,563 --> 00:26:28,033
Your papa was wrong.

338
00:26:28,111 --> 00:26:32,994
Life doesn't just pull you left and right.

339
00:26:33,607 --> 00:26:36,476
It also pulls you up and down.

340
00:26:48,121 --> 00:26:50,279
<i>I drank all night with my friends.</i>

341
00:26:50,810 --> 00:26:52,319
<i>And returned home in the morning.</i>

342
00:27:02,681 --> 00:27:04,447
I'm going for a jog.

343
00:27:12,287 --> 00:27:13,128
Sit.

344
00:27:17,334 --> 00:27:20,404
Sorry, sonny. I yelled at you publicly.

345
00:27:21,012 --> 00:27:25,423
I'm stressed, so couldn't control myself.

346
00:27:27,049 --> 00:27:28,088
A request...

347
00:27:29,332 --> 00:27:31,773
Please focus on your work.

348
00:27:31,853 --> 00:27:35,370
Your mother should feel proud
when she sees your first film.

349
00:27:36,410 --> 00:27:39,976
She may not be able to see your next.

350
00:27:41,097 --> 00:27:41,895
Why?

351
00:27:46,132 --> 00:27:48,497
She has cancer of the pancreas.

352
00:27:49,176 --> 00:27:52,775
I'm taking her to New York.
Sloan Hospital.

353
00:27:52,854 --> 00:27:55,500
Why didn't anyone tell me?

354
00:27:55,583 --> 00:27:58,899
She hid it from you
so your work won't suffer.

355
00:27:59,301 --> 00:28:01,898
She's been in pain all year.

356
00:28:02,337 --> 00:28:04,742
But acts fit in front of you.

357
00:28:04,823 --> 00:28:06,421
Where are you?

358
00:28:07,104 --> 00:28:09,223
In the dining. Want some tea?

359
00:28:09,302 --> 00:28:10,499
Half a cup.

360
00:28:10,900 --> 00:28:11,979
Hide it.

361
00:28:14,103 --> 00:28:15,465
Don't cry in her presence.

362
00:28:15,546 --> 00:28:18,421
She's acting. So must you.

363
00:28:19,824 --> 00:28:22,265
Up so early?

364
00:28:23,587 --> 00:28:25,874
Did you tell Sanju we're off to New York?

365
00:28:26,942 --> 00:28:30,110
What? Haven't shared the news?

366
00:28:31,388 --> 00:28:34,915
Take a deep breath.
You're gonna be shocked.

367
00:28:36,186 --> 00:28:39,112
I've been offered a Hollywood film.

368
00:28:39,869 --> 00:28:42,188
Now I'll mouth English dialogues.

369
00:28:44,670 --> 00:28:46,268
James Bond.

370
00:28:58,317 --> 00:29:01,233
I wish they had songs like our films.

371
00:29:01,673 --> 00:29:05,476
<i>This heart has lost its mate</i>

372
00:29:05,958 --> 00:29:09,875
<i>No one knows where my liver went</i>

373
00:29:10,716 --> 00:29:13,521
A song here, a dance there,

374
00:29:13,760 --> 00:29:15,480
and the Oscar's mine!

375
00:29:16,161 --> 00:29:18,162
You shouldn't have retired!

376
00:29:18,241 --> 00:29:21,160
Retired? I still act, don't I?

377
00:29:42,366 --> 00:29:44,286
<i>Dad took mom to New York.</i>

378
00:29:44,363 --> 00:29:46,725
<i>And I started spending more time with God.</i>

379
00:29:48,808 --> 00:29:52,807
I was 18 when I lost my parents
in a car crash.

380
00:29:52,887 --> 00:29:55,285
I was going to kill myself.

381
00:29:55,689 --> 00:29:57,731
A fakir saved me.

382
00:29:57,971 --> 00:30:01,728
He said, "The Lord who created pain,
also created a remedy."

383
00:30:02,369 --> 00:30:03,332
Here.

384
00:30:03,530 --> 00:30:06,454
Put it under your tongue.
It'll melt away all pain.

385
00:30:06,534 --> 00:30:09,620
He gets it from the Himalayas.
So it's expensive.

386
00:30:09,778 --> 00:30:12,052
But I'll send him the money.

387
00:30:37,298 --> 00:30:40,864
<i>The first time I did drugs,</i>
<i>was 'cause I was upset with dad.</i>

388
00:30:41,263 --> 00:30:43,991
<i>The second time, 'cause mom was dying.</i>

389
00:30:45,260 --> 00:30:48,387
<i>By the third time, I was an addict.</i>

390
00:30:50,668 --> 00:30:53,262
<i>Then I got the news</i>
<i>that mom was in a coma.</i>

391
00:30:53,381 --> 00:30:55,581
<i>Dad summoned me to America.</i>

392
00:30:55,662 --> 00:30:57,626
<i>I traveled with my sisters...</i>

393
00:30:57,787 --> 00:30:59,590
<i>and 20 grams of cocaine.</i>

394
00:31:02,665 --> 00:31:04,953
<i>Being caught at the airport,</i>
<i>would've meant</i>

395
00:31:05,272 --> 00:31:08,628
<i>20 years in prison... even for my sisters.</i>

396
00:31:09,197 --> 00:31:10,948
<i>But back then, 20 years in prison,</i>

397
00:31:11,027 --> 00:31:12,588
<i>versus 20 grams of cocaine...</i>

398
00:31:12,826 --> 00:31:14,790
<i>my choice was crystal clear.</i>

399
00:31:16,474 --> 00:31:18,440
<i>I was so irresponsible</i>

400
00:31:18,638 --> 00:31:20,589
<i>that instead of spending time with mom,</i>

401
00:31:20,669 --> 00:31:23,313
<i>I'd smoke away in the fire exit.</i>

402
00:31:23,553 --> 00:31:26,564
<i>Then one night, walked into my life...</i>

403
00:31:27,991 --> 00:31:30,758
<i>Mr. Kamlesh Kanhaiyalal Kapasi.</i>

404
00:31:48,882 --> 00:31:51,640
-What did you steal?
-Twins...

405
00:31:52,127 --> 00:31:55,839
-O Lord Ganesha!
-This is Jesus' jurisdiction.

406
00:31:56,241 --> 00:31:59,123
Lord Ganesha doesn't operate here.
What did you steal?

407
00:31:59,444 --> 00:32:02,481
I'd gone to keep the idol inside.

408
00:32:12,444 --> 00:32:16,247
I'm a fan of your parents.

409
00:32:16,891 --> 00:32:19,606
Thought Lord Ganesha
will heal your mother.

410
00:32:23,610 --> 00:32:24,731
But, what's "Twins"?

411
00:32:26,130 --> 00:32:29,089
Eggs. Back home we call them Twins.

412
00:32:31,696 --> 00:32:33,573
Hope "The Twins" haven't parted ways.

413
00:32:33,936 --> 00:32:35,138
They are out of shape.

414
00:32:37,450 --> 00:32:38,331
Come.

415
00:32:39,049 --> 00:32:41,815
-Where?
-To get The Twins back in shape.

416
00:33:17,584 --> 00:33:19,308
Ever seen a topless girl?

417
00:33:19,623 --> 00:33:21,300
Of course, I have.

418
00:33:21,620 --> 00:33:24,264
-Where? On TV?
-No, live.

419
00:33:24,468 --> 00:33:27,950
My physics teacher, back home...

420
00:33:28,346 --> 00:33:30,304
his mother slipped in the bathroom.

421
00:33:30,423 --> 00:33:33,268
I broke the door,
hauled her on my shoulder

422
00:33:33,349 --> 00:33:34,829
and put her in the ambulance.

423
00:33:34,986 --> 00:33:37,625
Stark naked... topless, bottomless.

424
00:33:37,906 --> 00:33:39,669
How old was she?

425
00:33:39,749 --> 00:33:41,309
Ninety. No, 91.

426
00:33:43,790 --> 00:33:45,431
I did see stuff. I'm not naive.

427
00:33:46,149 --> 00:33:48,392
-Ever had alcohol?
-Of course.

428
00:34:09,080 --> 00:34:10,845
There's a saying back home...

429
00:34:10,964 --> 00:34:13,122
"Jam-jam bam-bam."

430
00:34:13,599 --> 00:34:14,648
Translate that.

431
00:34:15,044 --> 00:34:16,563
"Jam-jam" is money.

432
00:34:16,762 --> 00:34:18,487
And "bam-bam"?

433
00:34:19,843 --> 00:34:21,040
Sex.

434
00:34:22,886 --> 00:34:26,484
Your jacket took away jam-jam,
I lost my bam-bam.

435
00:34:26,883 --> 00:34:29,564
You owe me a blonde.

436
00:34:35,286 --> 00:34:36,891
Cover me.

437
00:34:47,928 --> 00:34:49,135
Don't! You'll land in prison.

438
00:34:49,217 --> 00:34:50,571
Relax.

439
00:35:42,986 --> 00:35:43,954
Run!

440
00:35:58,915 --> 00:36:00,994
Stop joking. We could've been arrested.

441
00:36:01,155 --> 00:36:03,322
Noble cause, brother.

442
00:36:05,835 --> 00:36:09,676
Your mom's in the hospital
and you're snorting?

443
00:36:09,880 --> 00:36:12,003
Hey, Mr. Righteousness.

444
00:36:12,163 --> 00:36:14,074
We've been friends for just five minutes.

445
00:36:14,639 --> 00:36:17,235
-Control your emotions.
-Friendship?

446
00:36:17,516 --> 00:36:20,922
You aren't a good son!
How'll you be a good friend?

447
00:36:25,397 --> 00:36:27,526
Get lost! I don't need a friend.

448
00:36:34,280 --> 00:36:35,604
Hey, stop!

449
00:36:42,962 --> 00:36:44,451
I just can't quit.

450
00:36:49,206 --> 00:36:50,569
Alright, go!

451
00:36:51,164 --> 00:36:55,332
If my friend was on drugs,
I wouldn't abandon him.

452
00:36:55,410 --> 00:36:56,927
I'd thrash him till he quit.

453
00:37:06,132 --> 00:37:07,213
Throw it.

454
00:37:07,293 --> 00:37:09,733
-I'll quit tomorrow.
-Now.

455
00:37:09,892 --> 00:37:11,420
I promise, tomorrow.

456
00:37:12,457 --> 00:37:15,134
-Let go my twins.
-Let go the powder.

457
00:37:15,416 --> 00:37:17,491
-Twins first.
-Powder first.

458
00:37:17,772 --> 00:37:20,103
-I'm desperate.
-It's the time to fight.

459
00:37:20,463 --> 00:37:21,657
Say, "I'm a tiger."

460
00:37:21,855 --> 00:37:23,256
-Now, rorr.
-"Rorr"?

461
00:37:25,179 --> 00:37:25,975
Once more.

462
00:37:30,258 --> 00:37:33,180
I quit! I promise.

463
00:37:35,539 --> 00:37:39,455
Never abandon me, Master.
Such words of wisdom...

464
00:37:39,778 --> 00:37:42,978
Rorr, jam-jam bam-bam, twins.

465
00:37:43,939 --> 00:37:45,348
Guess what?

466
00:37:45,468 --> 00:37:46,946
You didn't twist my twins...

467
00:37:47,980 --> 00:37:49,062
but this.

468
00:37:57,586 --> 00:37:59,749
<i>I was seeking drugs in New York.</i>

469
00:37:59,826 --> 00:38:01,585
<i>Instead, I found a friend.</i>

470
00:38:01,665 --> 00:38:04,786
Kamlesh Kanhaiyalal Kapasi.
They call me Kamli.

471
00:38:04,986 --> 00:38:08,664
As Sex-spear has said, "What's in a name?"

472
00:38:09,185 --> 00:38:11,676
-Who?
-Sex-spear.

473
00:38:12,314 --> 00:38:13,703
William...

474
00:38:14,266 --> 00:38:16,471
-Sir, will you have snakes?
-Snakes?

475
00:38:16,748 --> 00:38:18,947
Snakes. There are lots in the hole.

476
00:38:19,712 --> 00:38:20,917
I'll get it, sir.

477
00:38:25,352 --> 00:38:29,197
<i>In his accent, snacks were "snakes"</i>
<i>and hall was "hole".</i>

478
00:38:29,438 --> 00:38:32,354
<i>He brought back our smiles.</i>

479
00:38:32,433 --> 00:38:37,202
<i>And miraculously,</i>
<i>his idol got mom out of coma.</i>

480
00:38:37,404 --> 00:38:38,873
Ready, everyone?

481
00:38:39,192 --> 00:38:40,956
Smile.

482
00:38:55,880 --> 00:39:00,438
At your film premiere,
I'll sit between father and son.

483
00:39:01,237 --> 00:39:04,363
As you appear on screen, I'll whistle.

484
00:39:09,001 --> 00:39:12,770
At your wedding, I'll dance on the table.

485
00:39:13,124 --> 00:39:15,121
Warn Ruby not to be embarrassed.

486
00:39:18,003 --> 00:39:22,561
<i>Mom didn't know Ruby wasn't talking to me.</i>

487
00:39:26,886 --> 00:39:28,531
<i>Mom didn't have much time left.</i>

488
00:39:28,936 --> 00:39:30,251
<i>I decided</i>

489
00:39:30,329 --> 00:39:34,369
<i>I'd apologize to Ruby's dad</i>
<i>and ask for her hand.</i>

490
00:39:35,046 --> 00:39:36,729
I love Ruby and I want to...

491
00:39:39,647 --> 00:39:41,371
I've come to apologize.

492
00:39:41,652 --> 00:39:44,449
-I misbehaved that day.
-It's alright, child.

493
00:39:44,611 --> 00:39:46,540
-A tipple often does that.
-No, Daddy.

494
00:39:47,098 --> 00:39:50,133
I wasn't just drunk...
I had also done cocaine.

495
00:39:50,577 --> 00:39:56,652
Let me confess. The next day I did LSD.

496
00:39:57,010 --> 00:39:59,180
But I've been clean for a month.

497
00:40:01,574 --> 00:40:02,659
Congratulations!

498
00:40:07,338 --> 00:40:08,580
I'll go meet Ruby.

499
00:40:09,376 --> 00:40:11,503
-Ruby.
-Wait.

500
00:40:11,824 --> 00:40:14,376
Meet her on the 22nd
at Hotel Sun and Sand,

501
00:40:14,454 --> 00:40:16,424
with these flowers.

502
00:40:16,862 --> 00:40:18,739
-What's on the 22nd?
-Wait.

503
00:40:25,504 --> 00:40:27,662
That's for your parents.

504
00:40:27,823 --> 00:40:29,830
And that's for you. Write your name.

505
00:40:29,909 --> 00:40:32,622
"Ruby weds..." Who's this Rustom?

506
00:40:35,662 --> 00:40:39,425
All this for a 10 rupee bill?
I'll glue it up.

507
00:40:39,505 --> 00:40:43,309
I'm glad you tore it. It led us to Rustom!

508
00:40:43,387 --> 00:40:46,518
He's a doctor in New York.
Not a junkie like you.

509
00:40:47,713 --> 00:40:49,024
Daddy, let me meet Ruby--

510
00:40:54,593 --> 00:40:56,749
Then what should I call you? Old fart?

511
00:40:57,146 --> 00:41:00,593
Meet Ruby over my dead body.

512
00:41:00,670 --> 00:41:02,471
Fine, I'll wait.

513
00:41:02,551 --> 00:41:03,395
For what?

514
00:41:03,478 --> 00:41:05,074
For you to die, old fart!

515
00:41:07,795 --> 00:41:09,713
Rascal! Scoundrel!

516
00:41:09,912 --> 00:41:12,120
Get out!

517
00:41:12,201 --> 00:41:14,154
I'll break your legs, you swine.

518
00:41:16,478 --> 00:41:20,683
<i>Every addict looks for an excuse</i>
<i>to start again.</i>

519
00:41:20,844 --> 00:41:23,074
<i>My excuse was Ruby.</i>

520
00:41:32,598 --> 00:41:37,041
<i>Ruby, Ruby, Ruby</i>
<i>Let's rendezvous</i>

521
00:41:44,362 --> 00:41:47,612
<i>To have you back</i>

522
00:41:48,246 --> 00:41:51,768
<i>Your old man I'll hack</i>

523
00:41:55,971 --> 00:41:59,407
<i>It's a win-win!</i>

524
00:41:59,488 --> 00:42:03,292
<i>He gets heaven, I get you</i>

525
00:42:05,135 --> 00:42:08,454
<i>The world has no heart</i>

526
00:42:08,534 --> 00:42:12,015
<i>So leave it, old fart</i>

527
00:42:12,659 --> 00:42:16,212
<i>Goodbye, old man! Just die, old man!</i>

528
00:42:16,452 --> 00:42:21,580
<i>Your daughter, don't worry</i>
<i>Once you're dead, we'll marry</i>

529
00:42:22,020 --> 00:42:25,937
<i>The sincerest prayers are always granted.</i>

530
00:42:26,853 --> 00:42:31,338
<i>The old man died</i>
<i>of a massive heart attack.</i>

531
00:42:31,495 --> 00:42:36,775
<i>The news was tragic. But I won't lie,</i>

532
00:42:36,857 --> 00:42:38,944
<i>I was ecstatic.</i>

533
00:42:39,625 --> 00:42:44,498
<i>Ruby, Ruby, Ruby</i>
<i>Get set to rendezvous</i>

534
00:42:51,585 --> 00:42:56,309
<i>Ruby, Ruby, Ruby</i>
<i>You and I, we'll rendezvous</i>

535
00:42:58,178 --> 00:43:02,021
<i>This was my chance to win back Ruby.</i>

536
00:43:06,741 --> 00:43:10,825
<i>I had to show her,</i>
<i>I was more reliable than her fiancé.</i>

537
00:43:13,754 --> 00:43:17,949
<i>A minor problem... I was stoned.</i>

538
00:43:18,030 --> 00:43:19,548
Papa!

539
00:43:20,107 --> 00:43:22,035
Don't abandon us, Papa.

540
00:43:22,237 --> 00:43:25,510
-Sanju, that's not papa.
-Wake up.

541
00:43:25,954 --> 00:43:27,110
That's not papa!

542
00:43:31,397 --> 00:43:33,792
Ha! I wondered how he'd shrunk so much.

543
00:43:38,235 --> 00:43:40,870
Is this our papa?

544
00:43:42,915 --> 00:43:44,953
Papa!

545
00:43:45,434 --> 00:43:47,645
Why did you abandon us?

546
00:43:47,801 --> 00:43:49,633
Wake up. Try!

547
00:43:52,918 --> 00:43:54,356
He isn't waking up.

548
00:43:55,039 --> 00:43:56,926
Mummy, don't cry.

549
00:43:57,046 --> 00:43:59,277
Your son-in-law is with you.

550
00:44:02,719 --> 00:44:05,248
Have you read the Holy Gita?

551
00:44:05,885 --> 00:44:08,804
"Everything happens for the best."
Superb!

552
00:44:09,604 --> 00:44:12,163
"Nothing we create...

553
00:44:12,527 --> 00:44:15,319
so nothing should we mourn."

554
00:44:15,960 --> 00:44:19,043
Did you create this old man?
Gave him birth?

555
00:44:24,002 --> 00:44:25,406
Let her grieve.

556
00:44:25,487 --> 00:44:28,165
When my puppy died, I was bawling.

557
00:44:28,245 --> 00:44:31,889
A full-grown husband's exit
deserves howling.

558
00:44:31,968 --> 00:44:33,486
Take your time, Mummy.

559
00:44:33,566 --> 00:44:37,609
But remember, only the body perishes.

560
00:44:37,688 --> 00:44:39,379
The soul is eternal.

561
00:44:39,617 --> 00:44:41,089
Away with this body.

562
00:44:41,367 --> 00:44:43,253
Focus on the soul.

563
00:44:46,854 --> 00:44:49,018
Papa conked and you say, "All okay?"

564
00:44:50,408 --> 00:44:53,013
How shall we dispose the body?

565
00:44:53,133 --> 00:44:55,256
Bury it? Cremate it?

566
00:44:57,540 --> 00:44:59,694
God, that's not our papa.

567
00:44:59,774 --> 00:45:02,575
Move that body. It's freaking confusing.

568
00:45:03,134 --> 00:45:04,097
Move it.

569
00:45:04,823 --> 00:45:05,903
So, Ruby...

570
00:45:10,497 --> 00:45:11,736
What did I do?

571
00:45:16,215 --> 00:45:18,900
No one can tell it's secondhand.

572
00:45:19,299 --> 00:45:20,699
A very fair price.

573
00:45:21,504 --> 00:45:22,908
Five hundred dollars.

574
00:45:25,141 --> 00:45:26,183
What's this?

575
00:45:26,626 --> 00:45:28,181
Robbed a beggar?

576
00:45:28,262 --> 00:45:30,993
Robbed a barber! He cuts his own hair.

577
00:45:31,072 --> 00:45:33,062
Puts three dollars in the piggy bank.

578
00:45:33,181 --> 00:45:37,104
-Who's gonna count this?
-Call from India. It's Sanju!

579
00:45:37,183 --> 00:45:39,191
Awesome!

580
00:45:41,306 --> 00:45:46,546
Sanju, perfect timing.
I'm buying my first car.

581
00:45:46,626 --> 00:45:48,434
I need you here, bro.

582
00:45:50,906 --> 00:45:52,990
Ruby's getting married.

583
00:45:53,070 --> 00:45:54,267
<i>Please come.</i>

584
00:45:54,428 --> 00:45:57,679
-You snorting again?
-No. I swear.

585
00:45:57,756 --> 00:46:00,151
Please... come down.

586
00:46:00,753 --> 00:46:02,309
Sanju... Hello?

587
00:46:06,478 --> 00:46:08,593
Sir, no need to count.

588
00:46:08,755 --> 00:46:11,034
-The car will have to wait.
-Why?

589
00:46:11,114 --> 00:46:14,283
Need to buy a ticket to India.

590
00:46:16,914 --> 00:46:17,997
Sorry, sir.

591
00:46:18,239 --> 00:46:20,074
Didn't want the car? Why make me count?

592
00:46:28,398 --> 00:46:29,518
Hello, Ruby.

593
00:46:29,798 --> 00:46:32,721
I'm Kamlesh Kanhaiyalal Kapasi.
Sanju's friend.

594
00:46:33,517 --> 00:46:35,363
Sir, can you go inside?

595
00:46:35,604 --> 00:46:36,680
Take a loo break.

596
00:46:38,481 --> 00:46:41,282
-Need to discuss a private matter.
-Come.

597
00:46:45,243 --> 00:46:48,533
Whatever the matter,
say it in front of me.

598
00:46:48,932 --> 00:46:50,921
It'll upset you.

599
00:46:51,162 --> 00:46:54,084
Take a stroll outside. Lovely weather.

600
00:46:58,012 --> 00:46:59,325
Really?

601
00:47:02,726 --> 00:47:04,852
Then name Ruby's favorite animal.

602
00:47:10,611 --> 00:47:11,847
You live in New York?

603
00:47:12,408 --> 00:47:15,813
Ask any jeweler there...

604
00:47:16,011 --> 00:47:18,132
They'll all say... "Penguin".

605
00:47:19,492 --> 00:47:20,892
-Know why?
-Why?

606
00:47:21,011 --> 00:47:24,455
For a month, Sanju hopped
from jeweler to jeweler

607
00:47:24,612 --> 00:47:28,414
for a wedding necklace
with a penguin pendant.

608
00:47:28,934 --> 00:47:30,418
And finally got it!

609
00:47:30,538 --> 00:47:32,344
But when he returned to India,

610
00:47:32,462 --> 00:47:34,938
he discovered that you were engaged.

611
00:47:35,620 --> 00:47:38,776
He was shattered, so took to drugs again.

612
00:47:38,858 --> 00:47:41,024
But yesterday, he braved up.

613
00:47:41,102 --> 00:47:43,216
Flushed all the drugs down the drain.

614
00:47:43,658 --> 00:47:45,938
Swore never to touch them again.

615
00:47:46,018 --> 00:47:48,669
He prayed, "Lord, bring Ruby back."

616
00:47:49,468 --> 00:47:51,256
Sanju's back.

617
00:47:51,739 --> 00:47:52,904
Can you come back?

618
00:47:54,780 --> 00:47:57,149
The wedding date, venue... it's all set.

619
00:47:57,230 --> 00:47:59,381
Nothing changes, except the groom.

620
00:47:59,459 --> 00:48:01,304
The wedding cards have been printed.

621
00:48:01,386 --> 00:48:04,383
We'll put a "Sanju" sticker
over your name.

622
00:48:04,464 --> 00:48:05,955
Don't sweat the small stuff.

623
00:48:11,107 --> 00:48:14,954
Ruby, in America
there'll be no house help.

624
00:48:15,154 --> 00:48:17,306
You'll be cleaning, mopping, washing...

625
00:48:17,467 --> 00:48:19,909
Imagine washing his sweaty underpants!

626
00:48:21,548 --> 00:48:23,037
I told you, you'd be upset.

627
00:48:23,117 --> 00:48:26,790
Sanju will be at the Marriage Registrar's,
tomorrow at 4 p.m.

628
00:48:41,002 --> 00:48:42,712
Mister, what's her favorite food?

629
00:48:44,997 --> 00:48:47,274
Waffles. Sanju knows.

630
00:48:49,046 --> 00:48:50,358
Her favorite film?

631
00:48:51,512 --> 00:48:52,878
<i>Mary Poppins.</i>

632
00:48:52,998 --> 00:48:55,796
Sanju knows. You have no clue.

633
00:48:56,318 --> 00:48:57,647
Ruby, 4 p.m. tomorrow.

634
00:48:58,046 --> 00:49:00,074
The Marriage Registrar's office.

635
00:49:15,409 --> 00:49:17,400
Where did you get money for this?

636
00:49:17,721 --> 00:49:19,766
Your wallet, checks... They're with me.

637
00:49:22,407 --> 00:49:24,611
The wedding necklace...

638
00:49:24,731 --> 00:49:25,763
What about it?

639
00:49:25,882 --> 00:49:28,248
I sold it to God.

640
00:49:39,208 --> 00:49:42,451
-Where's he?
-He isn't home.

641
00:49:42,529 --> 00:49:44,330
<i>Woo-hoo!</i>

642
00:49:57,217 --> 00:50:00,975
I wait at the Registrar's office
and you get stoned here?

643
00:50:01,495 --> 00:50:05,054
No sweat. We'll marry tomorrow.

644
00:50:08,456 --> 00:50:12,138
You'd flushed the drugs!
Fished them out again?

645
00:50:18,379 --> 00:50:21,062
Where's the wedding necklace?

646
00:50:22,622 --> 00:50:24,150
Where is it?

647
00:50:24,631 --> 00:50:26,821
Where's the bloody necklace?

648
00:50:35,663 --> 00:50:37,027
The wedding necklace.

649
00:51:01,753 --> 00:51:03,471
Please wait, Ruby.

650
00:51:05,590 --> 00:51:07,439
I'm sorry...

651
00:51:08,196 --> 00:51:09,151
Yuck.

652
00:51:09,390 --> 00:51:12,912
He's not in his senses.
Won't remember a thing tomorrow!

653
00:51:12,992 --> 00:51:16,401
I swear, he did buy the wedding necklace.

654
00:51:18,594 --> 00:51:20,795
He's too far gone

655
00:51:21,074 --> 00:51:23,601
and to expect you'll hang on is not right.

656
00:51:25,044 --> 00:51:28,280
You move on, I'm with him.

657
00:51:38,401 --> 00:51:39,599
Kamlesh.

658
00:51:39,961 --> 00:51:40,886
Yes, Ruby.

659
00:51:40,965 --> 00:51:43,043
Don't ever tell him what he did.

660
00:51:43,561 --> 00:51:45,204
He'll be devastated.

661
00:51:45,486 --> 00:51:46,763
Tell him...

662
00:51:47,841 --> 00:51:50,211
that rotten Ruby never showed up.

663
00:52:09,248 --> 00:52:10,851
You've been drinking?

664
00:52:10,971 --> 00:52:14,652
What I wanna say needs courage.

665
00:52:15,454 --> 00:52:17,931
So I downed a couple.

666
00:52:18,771 --> 00:52:19,975
Tell me.

667
00:52:21,452 --> 00:52:24,502
Your son will die before your wife!

668
00:52:24,981 --> 00:52:28,015
-He can't handle his life.
-Why?

669
00:52:28,736 --> 00:52:31,614
He sees you nursing your ailing wife.

670
00:52:32,298 --> 00:52:36,737
Any responsibility at home,
film industry, society...

671
00:52:37,098 --> 00:52:39,575
he sees you never shirk it.

672
00:52:42,266 --> 00:52:44,056
And your son...

673
00:52:45,420 --> 00:52:47,778
He's an ordinary guy.

674
00:52:48,058 --> 00:52:51,067
No goals, no purpose in life.

675
00:52:51,148 --> 00:52:55,621
He says,
"There are three things to life, bro."

676
00:52:56,860 --> 00:52:59,750
"C, B, S."

677
00:53:00,584 --> 00:53:03,706
"Chew, brew and scr..."

678
00:53:09,225 --> 00:53:12,706
The problem is, you want him to be you!

679
00:53:14,545 --> 00:53:15,671
He's buried...

680
00:53:16,034 --> 00:53:19,306
buried under the weight of your legacy!

681
00:53:19,788 --> 00:53:23,549
He knows, however hard he toils,
he can never be as great.

682
00:53:23,630 --> 00:53:26,390
So, he doesn't even try.

683
00:53:28,390 --> 00:53:31,230
Feels a hero with nobodies like me.

684
00:53:31,309 --> 00:53:34,717
"Yo, Kamli...", "Hey, Kamli..."

685
00:53:38,433 --> 00:53:41,357
What should I do, Kamlesh?

686
00:53:41,436 --> 00:53:42,919
Sir, you...

687
00:53:47,437 --> 00:53:49,195
Just be his friend.

688
00:53:49,275 --> 00:53:51,122
Sit with him.

689
00:53:51,522 --> 00:53:52,875
Drink with him.

690
00:53:52,954 --> 00:53:55,519
Use a few cuss words, and say...

691
00:53:55,597 --> 00:54:00,205
"Sonny, it's okay to be ordinary."

692
00:54:00,681 --> 00:54:02,761
"You don't have to be Sunil Dutt."

693
00:54:02,841 --> 00:54:05,518
"It's okay to be Sanjay Dutt.”

694
00:54:05,997 --> 00:54:09,443
Sir, please save him.

695
00:54:11,203 --> 00:54:12,244
If he dies,

696
00:54:12,324 --> 00:54:15,968
whom will I tell, "Let go my twins"?

697
00:54:18,881 --> 00:54:21,445
Please, sir, save him.

698
00:54:24,249 --> 00:54:25,852
Save him.

699
00:54:45,130 --> 00:54:47,254
I showed the distributors your film.

700
00:54:47,372 --> 00:54:52,216
They went crazy...
"What a freaking actor!"

701
00:54:57,572 --> 00:54:59,260
Has mom seen the posters?

702
00:54:59,542 --> 00:55:01,296
She's in hospital.

703
00:55:01,813 --> 00:55:02,694
What happened?

704
00:55:04,059 --> 00:55:06,253
She slipped into a coma again.

705
00:55:06,334 --> 00:55:09,937
-I just met her yesterday!
-No, day before.

706
00:55:10,017 --> 00:55:13,698
You've woken up after two days. It's okay.

707
00:55:17,864 --> 00:55:19,579
I've spoken to the doctors.

708
00:55:19,660 --> 00:55:22,660
They recommend a rehab center in America.

709
00:55:22,978 --> 00:55:23,819
Ready?

710
00:55:24,545 --> 00:55:25,510
No!

711
00:55:25,747 --> 00:55:27,181
Please don't send me there, Dad.

712
00:55:27,342 --> 00:55:28,983
Just a few days, sonny.

713
00:55:29,465 --> 00:55:30,582
No.

714
00:55:34,710 --> 00:55:37,987
Come out. We won't send you anywhere.

715
00:55:38,068 --> 00:55:40,783
I had one cigarette, you packed me off
to boarding school.

716
00:55:40,864 --> 00:55:43,591
I was just six.
Couldn't even tie my shoelaces.

717
00:55:43,671 --> 00:55:44,905
I missed mom.

718
00:55:46,749 --> 00:55:47,628
Please come out.

719
00:55:48,826 --> 00:55:50,551
I won't go anywhere.

720
00:55:50,834 --> 00:55:53,228
I'll stay with mom in the hospital!

721
00:55:58,026 --> 00:56:00,915
<i>Dad agreed... on one condition.</i>

722
00:56:01,037 --> 00:56:04,195
<i>That I wouldn't do drugs in the hospital.</i>

723
00:56:04,472 --> 00:56:05,831
<i>And I promised.</i>

724
00:56:06,431 --> 00:56:08,760
<i>I started spending</i>
<i>every night at the hospital.</i>

725
00:56:09,240 --> 00:56:11,755
<i>I'd stare at mom for hours.</i>

726
00:56:12,074 --> 00:56:14,433
<i>I'd hold her hand and talk to her.</i>

727
00:56:14,792 --> 00:56:16,760
The premiere's next week.

728
00:56:16,921 --> 00:56:18,201
Won't you come?

729
00:56:18,636 --> 00:56:19,592
Get up, Mom.

730
00:56:19,915 --> 00:56:21,678
You gotta see me act.

731
00:56:22,037 --> 00:56:23,875
You'll be proud, Mom.

732
00:56:24,921 --> 00:56:25,845
Mom.

733
00:56:28,235 --> 00:56:29,400
<i>Then one day...</i>

734
00:56:29,600 --> 00:56:30,919
<i>I couldn't resist.</i>

735
00:56:45,018 --> 00:56:46,338
<i>Sanju...</i>

736
00:58:01,068 --> 00:58:03,112
<i>Mom never saw my film.</i>

737
00:58:03,829 --> 00:58:07,354
<i>She died three days before the premiere.</i>

738
00:58:07,912 --> 00:58:09,193
<i>She'd left a note...</i>

739
00:58:09,273 --> 00:58:12,074
<i>"Even if I'm gone, the show must go on."</i>

740
00:58:19,235 --> 00:58:24,600
<i>They call me Rocky</i>
<i>Yes, my name is Rocky!</i>

741
00:58:25,760 --> 00:58:32,282
<i>Friend and foe</i>
<i>To both I say hello</i>

742
00:58:33,122 --> 00:58:39,439
<i>Friend and foe</i>
<i>To both I say hello</i>

743
00:58:40,884 --> 00:58:46,323
<i>They call me Rocky</i>
<i>Yes, my name is Rocky!</i>

744
00:58:49,045 --> 00:58:50,725
-Congratulations.
-Thank you.

745
00:58:52,205 --> 00:58:55,003
Excuse me, Mr. Dutt.
Is anyone sitting here?

746
00:58:55,923 --> 00:58:58,648
Yes... my wife.

747
00:59:20,411 --> 00:59:22,772
<i>Sanju, you'll be a film star!</i>

748
00:59:24,533 --> 00:59:26,972
<i>Dad worries a lot about you.</i>

749
00:59:27,092 --> 00:59:29,852
<i>I've been offered a Hollywood film.</i>

750
00:59:30,015 --> 00:59:32,657
<i>At your wedding, I'll dance on the table.</i>

751
00:59:37,616 --> 00:59:38,814
Sanju.

752
