01:21:04,925 --> 01:21:08,767
My aunt's cousin is a banker.
You'll be done in a jiffy.

992
01:21:09,042 --> 01:21:11,682
-You need an account, too?
-No, I have many accounts.

993
01:21:20,365 --> 01:21:22,048
What's all this?

994
01:21:22,688 --> 01:21:24,136
All for you.

995
01:21:26,127 --> 01:21:29,168
This pink t-shirt, sweater,

996
01:21:30,931 --> 01:21:32,056
lin-jer-ree...

997
01:21:34,809 --> 01:21:39,172
This pink nightie, just for you! Try it.

998
01:21:39,374 --> 01:21:44,171
No, I'll stick to the t-shirt.

999
01:21:49,739 --> 01:21:50,819
One moment.

1000
01:21:52,614 --> 01:21:54,855
Do you know why
nighties are called nighties?

1001
01:21:55,654 --> 01:21:56,539
Why?

1002
01:21:57,459 --> 01:21:59,621
'Cause they are worn at night.

1003
01:22:01,097 --> 01:22:05,859
Scriptures say,
hour and attire must match.

1004
01:22:20,860 --> 01:22:23,105
I've got her in the nightie.

1005
01:22:23,468 --> 01:22:25,864
-Your job is to get her out of it.
-Done!

1006
01:22:27,421 --> 01:22:31,108
Don't overdrink,
or there'll be no bam-bam.

1007
01:22:32,511 --> 01:22:35,626
I'm out of here. Freshen up.

1008
01:22:35,786 --> 01:22:36,867
I'll change, too.

1009
01:23:00,756 --> 01:23:04,153
<i>On a journey to the moon</i>

1010
01:23:05,595 --> 01:23:09,196
<i>Let's dance, let's swoon</i>

1011
01:23:10,235 --> 01:23:13,678
<i>It's one night's delight</i>

1012
01:23:15,041 --> 01:23:17,678
<i>Then our paths will divide</i>

1013
01:23:19,358 --> 01:23:22,921
<i>On a journey to the moon</i>

1014
01:23:24,164 --> 01:23:27,597
<i>Let's dance, let's swoon</i>

1015
01:23:28,761 --> 01:23:32,002
<i>Just one night's delight</i>

1016
01:23:33,409 --> 01:23:36,481
<i>Come, set me alight</i>

1017
01:23:37,041 --> 01:23:38,281
Kamli...

1018
01:23:43,088 --> 01:23:45,966
Kamli, wake up.

1019
01:23:46,127 --> 01:23:47,206
Get up.

1020
01:23:48,447 --> 01:23:50,372
Time for bam-bam.

1021
01:23:50,573 --> 01:23:51,887
Wake up. You're a tiger.

1022
01:23:52,167 --> 01:23:54,207
Roar!

1023
01:23:54,567 --> 01:23:55,486
Come on.

1024
01:24:10,490 --> 01:24:14,853
<i>You are no saint</i>

1025
01:24:15,176 --> 01:24:19,052
<i>Nor am I</i>

1026
01:24:19,854 --> 01:24:24,219
<i>It's one night's delight</i>

1027
01:24:24,501 --> 01:24:28,457
<i>Let's not be uptight</i>

1028
01:24:32,299 --> 01:24:36,417
<i>On a journey to the moon</i>

1029
01:24:37,178 --> 01:24:41,304
<i>Let's dance, let's swoon</i>

1030
01:24:41,864 --> 01:24:45,901
<i>Just one night's delight</i>

1031
01:24:46,421 --> 01:24:50,228
<i>Come, set me alight</i>

1032
01:25:04,785 --> 01:25:06,952
Baby, you ready?

1033
01:25:07,031 --> 01:25:08,512
Have breakfast, Kamli.

1034
01:25:08,833 --> 01:25:11,348
-You're meeting some girls today.
-I have a girlfriend.

1035
01:25:11,429 --> 01:25:14,229
Forget her. She's a floozy.

1036
01:25:14,309 --> 01:25:17,356
-Shush... she'll hear you.
-She's gone.

1037
01:25:17,874 --> 01:25:20,350
You were very irresponsible last night!

1038
01:25:20,711 --> 01:25:23,192
You passed out and I had to bam-bam...

1039
01:25:23,513 --> 01:25:25,916
and then wrap up your pink store.

1040
01:25:27,273 --> 01:25:29,712
Chill, I'll set it up
for the next attempt.

1041
01:25:29,790 --> 01:25:32,475
Tell me you're lying.

1042
01:25:33,479 --> 01:25:37,034
I was checking her loyalty towards you.

1043
01:25:37,356 --> 01:25:41,641
I held her hand,
she rubbed it with her thumb.

1044
01:25:41,962 --> 01:25:44,558
That's all she does.

1045
01:25:44,877 --> 01:25:47,038
Never goes further.

1046
01:25:47,997 --> 01:25:49,600
With me, she went further, bro.

1047
01:25:50,564 --> 01:25:52,840
I said, "Nightie."

1048
01:25:55,598 --> 01:25:56,838
She took it off?

1049
01:26:03,082 --> 01:26:05,002
It was clear,
she can't be my sister-in-law.

1050
01:26:05,882 --> 01:26:07,606
No one cheats on my best friend!

1051
01:26:08,492 --> 01:26:11,683
It was guilt-free bam-bam.
What's her name?

1052
01:26:12,243 --> 01:26:14,082
You slept with her
and don't know her name?

1053
01:26:14,161 --> 01:26:16,247
Name after the game? Bad manners!

1054
01:26:16,329 --> 01:26:18,365
You swine!

1055
01:26:19,567 --> 01:26:22,765
I've unveiled her true colors.

1056
01:26:22,846 --> 01:26:25,454
You should be grateful.

1057
01:26:26,652 --> 01:26:27,768
<i>Hey, Sanju.</i>

1058
01:26:28,249 --> 01:26:30,646
<i>Your pop's buddying up to the Muslims.</i>

1059
01:26:30,968 --> 01:26:33,013
-Drill sense into him.
-Who the hell...?

1060
01:26:33,095 --> 01:26:35,532
<i>You half-Muslim!</i>

1061
01:26:35,611 --> 01:26:38,731
<i>Your sister is sizzling hot.</i>
<i>Shall I get her raped?</i>

1062
01:26:39,009 --> 01:26:39,852
Hey!

1063
01:26:41,979 --> 01:26:44,733
<i>It's a stone. Could've been a grenade.</i>

1064
01:26:45,052 --> 01:26:48,530
<i>Your pop's loading trucks</i>
<i>with relief material, right?</i>

1065
01:26:48,935 --> 01:26:53,015
<i>-I'll bump him off.</i>
<i>-Hello!</i>

1066
01:27:07,624 --> 01:27:10,219
-Let's get out of here.
-We've got a threat call.

1067
01:27:10,421 --> 01:27:13,139
You wake up late. I've already got five.

1068
01:27:13,339 --> 01:27:15,141
Barking dogs seldom bite.

1069
01:27:15,261 --> 01:27:17,388
Out here you can be shot.

1070
01:27:17,469 --> 01:27:18,503
We'll shield him.

1071
01:27:19,142 --> 01:27:20,783
We'll take the bullet.

1072
01:27:20,863 --> 01:27:24,625
We'll defend Mr. Dutt
till our last breath.

1073
01:27:24,706 --> 01:27:26,630
With that toy? Does it even work?

1074
01:27:26,709 --> 01:27:28,464
Yes, it does.

1075
01:27:34,111 --> 01:27:36,667
When did you last fire it? World War II?

1076
01:27:37,068 --> 01:27:38,467
Stop it, Sanju.

1077
01:27:38,546 --> 01:27:40,264
Hurry, load the truck.

1078
01:27:40,588 --> 01:27:42,754
Reason with dad. He never listens to me.

1079
01:27:42,874 --> 01:27:45,867
Look at him, and then at yourself.

1080
01:27:45,947 --> 01:27:47,429
He helps strangers.

1081
01:27:47,509 --> 01:27:50,635
While you bam-bam your best friend's girl.

1082
01:28:12,034 --> 01:28:14,955
<i>Hey, Kamli, remember the strip club?</i>

1083
01:28:15,680 --> 01:28:18,243
I lost out on a chick for your jacket.

1084
01:28:18,722 --> 01:28:22,037
<i>Remember, you owed me a blonde.</i>

1085
01:28:22,436 --> 01:28:24,880
Let's say Pinky is the blonde,
and we're square!

1086
01:28:26,046 --> 01:28:28,000
<i>I'm in New York on the 22nd.</i>

1087
01:28:28,082 --> 01:28:29,920
I'll wait outside the same club.

1088
01:28:31,680 --> 01:28:32,722
Wear that red jacket

1089
01:28:33,402 --> 01:28:35,568
<i>and I'll know you've forgiven me.</i>

1090
01:28:38,603 --> 01:28:40,083
Kamli, please forgive me.

1091
01:28:42,930 --> 01:28:43,772
Kamli...

1092
01:28:47,485 --> 01:28:52,931
<i>They say, "Life is what happens</i>
<i>when you're making other plans."</i>

1093
01:28:53,249 --> 01:28:57,727
<i>While he was planning his trip,</i>
<i>life had other plans.</i>

1094
01:29:18,221 --> 01:29:20,375
<i>Twelve bombs exploded that day.</i>

1095
01:29:20,454 --> 01:29:23,295
<i>250 people died. 800 were injured.</i>

1096
01:29:23,374 --> 01:29:25,781
<i>Police investigations revealed a name...</i>

1097
01:29:26,183 --> 01:29:27,461
<i>Tiger Memon.</i>

1098
01:29:28,017 --> 01:29:30,497
<i>In the riots following</i>
<i>the Babri mosque demolition,</i>

1099
01:29:30,576 --> 01:29:33,940
<i>Tiger Memon's office was burnt down.</i>
<i>He struck back.</i>

1100
01:29:34,863 --> 01:29:38,017
<i>As the truth unfolded, many were arrested.</i>

1101
01:29:39,537 --> 01:29:41,864
Kamlesh, read the news?

1102
01:29:44,107 --> 01:29:44,983
No. Why?

1103
01:29:45,062 --> 01:29:47,340
Your friend was involved
in the Bombay bomb blasts.

1104
01:29:48,220 --> 01:29:49,422
He's been arrested.

1105
01:29:49,499 --> 01:29:51,788
He had an AK-56 rifle.

1106
01:29:55,624 --> 01:29:58,464
Did you possess an AK-56 rifle?

1107
01:29:58,865 --> 01:29:59,788
No, sir.

1108
01:30:07,507 --> 01:30:11,308
Did you possess an AK-56?

1109
01:30:11,709 --> 01:30:12,908
I'll tell you, sir.

1110
01:30:13,428 --> 01:30:15,108
I'll tell you everything...

1111
01:30:15,828 --> 01:30:17,394
but please don't tell dad.

1112
01:30:27,997 --> 01:30:29,831
-Babu?
-Kamli.

1113
01:30:31,272 --> 01:30:34,560
I knew you'd come.

1114
01:30:34,960 --> 01:30:36,161
I'm glad.

1115
01:30:36,756 --> 01:30:40,553
Sir, I'm sure the AK-56 charges are bogus.

1116
01:30:44,763 --> 01:30:47,320
-Here's Sanju's confession.
-Read it.

1117
01:30:56,118 --> 01:30:59,120
Dad would send relief material
to riot victims.

1118
01:30:59,562 --> 01:31:01,007
Majority of them were Muslims.

1119
01:31:02,762 --> 01:31:04,881
Some people didn't approve.

1120
01:31:05,681 --> 01:31:07,200
They thought dad was pro-Muslim.

1121
01:31:08,809 --> 01:31:10,330
That's when the threats started...

1122
01:31:11,604 --> 01:31:14,404
to murder us and rape my sisters.

1123
01:31:15,203 --> 01:31:16,447
I was terrified.

1124
01:31:17,125 --> 01:31:20,488
Then there were two attacks on dad.

1125
01:31:20,928 --> 01:31:23,404
I requested special protection,
but was denied.

1126
01:31:24,286 --> 01:31:27,015
I feared a mob attack any time.

1127
01:31:28,409 --> 01:31:31,448
Hanif and Samir, producers of my film...

1128
01:31:32,327 --> 01:31:36,255
suggested I keep... an assault rifle,
for protection.

1129
01:31:46,052 --> 01:31:49,773
<i>In January, Samir, Hanif,</i>
<i>and Salem came home.</i>

1130
01:32:17,260 --> 01:32:20,302
<i>They gave me three rifles</i>
<i>and some bullets,</i>

1131
01:32:20,381 --> 01:32:22,423
<i>which I kept in my car.</i>

1132
01:32:25,625 --> 01:32:27,150
<i>Soon, I panicked.</i>

1133
01:32:28,428 --> 01:32:32,422
I'll keep only one rifle
till the riots end.

1134
01:32:32,543 --> 01:32:34,586
Please take away the rest.

1135
01:32:35,191 --> 01:32:36,712
<i>They came back two days later.</i>

1136
01:32:37,191 --> 01:32:41,708
<i>I returned two rifles.</i>
<i>Kept one rifle and 250 bullets.</i>

1137
01:32:43,674 --> 01:32:46,909
<i>On 2nd April, I went to Mauritius</i>
<i>for a film shoot.</i>

1138
01:32:47,429 --> 01:32:50,469
<i>I got news of Hanif and Samir's arrest.</i>

1139
01:32:50,790 --> 01:32:54,513
<i>I feared they'd rat me out.</i>

1140
01:32:55,394 --> 01:32:57,390
<i>I called my friend, Yusuf Nulwala.</i>

1141
01:32:58,270 --> 01:33:01,117
Yusuf, go to my house.

1142
01:33:02,161 --> 01:33:03,753
<i>Go to my room.</i>

1143
01:33:04,315 --> 01:33:06,394
<i>You'll find a black bag.</i>

1144
01:33:09,076 --> 01:33:11,321
<i>There's some stuff in it.</i>

1145
01:33:11,718 --> 01:33:13,195
<i>Destroy it.</i>

1146
01:33:27,567 --> 01:33:29,003
<i>Then one day, dad called.</i>

1147
01:33:29,882 --> 01:33:33,401
The papers say,
you possess an AK-56 rifle.

1148
01:33:33,920 --> 01:33:35,525
AK-56? No, Dad!

1149
01:33:35,686 --> 01:33:38,163
I've got you a meeting
with the Police Commissioner.

1150
01:33:38,283 --> 01:33:39,361
Come to Bombay.

1151
01:33:40,682 --> 01:33:43,725
<i>Dad informed the cops about my arrival,</i>

1152
01:33:43,970 --> 01:33:47,804
<i>and assured them he'll get me</i>
<i>to the police station.</i>

1153
01:33:47,924 --> 01:33:49,165
<i>But...</i>

1154
01:33:53,132 --> 01:33:54,253
Mr. Sanjay Dutt.

1155
01:34:01,896 --> 01:34:03,850
Deliver the luggage to his father.

1156
01:34:04,929 --> 01:34:06,009
Come with me.

1157
01:34:06,170 --> 01:34:07,930
-What's the problem, officer?
-Come.

1158
01:34:09,132 --> 01:34:10,417
Sir, what happened?

1159
01:34:12,175 --> 01:34:13,373
Get in.

1160
01:34:23,814 --> 01:34:26,776
Last time, we won the fight against drugs.

1161
01:34:27,862 --> 01:34:32,577
But this time...
the battle will be tougher.

1162
01:34:34,056 --> 01:34:37,503
-I'll need you, son.
-I'm not going anywhere, sir.

1163
01:34:38,179 --> 01:34:40,579
The "snakes" are in the "hole."

1164
01:34:41,058 --> 01:34:42,221
Grab a bite.

1165
01:34:43,741 --> 01:34:45,347
Sleep in Sanju's room.

1166
01:34:46,624 --> 01:34:48,061
I'll be here for a while.

1167
01:34:53,588 --> 01:34:54,669
Switch off the fan.

1168
01:34:55,266 --> 01:34:56,823
Sir, it's hot.

1169
01:34:58,941 --> 01:35:01,226
He sleeps without a fan, too.

1170
01:35:25,471 --> 01:35:27,277
<i>For security reasons,</i>

1171
01:35:27,358 --> 01:35:32,514
<i>Sanju was kept in isolation</i>
<i>in a windowless cell.</i>

1172
01:35:33,113 --> 01:35:36,398
<i>His only companions were ants.</i>

1173
01:35:36,640 --> 01:35:39,316
It's been seven days, soldiers.

1174
01:35:39,993 --> 01:35:41,476
When will I get bail?

1175
01:35:44,921 --> 01:35:46,481
Tell me.

1176
01:35:47,719 --> 01:35:48,759
Please...

1177
01:36:08,484 --> 01:36:10,409
Sir, the pot is overflowing.

1178
01:36:11,209 --> 01:36:12,408
Sir.

1179
01:36:17,807 --> 01:36:18,727
Please help!

1180
01:36:23,247 --> 01:36:24,366
Help!

1181
01:36:32,090 --> 01:36:36,575
<i>He suffered inside prison</i>
<i>and his dad, outside.</i>

1182
01:36:39,693 --> 01:36:41,171
Look, the terrorist's pop.

1183
01:37:01,536 --> 01:37:02,422
Come.

1184
01:37:06,177 --> 01:37:07,537
Give him a shave.

1185
01:37:09,660 --> 01:37:11,905
You're done.

1186
01:37:12,463 --> 01:37:14,301
Come, wash your face.

1187
01:37:15,580 --> 01:37:16,461
You speak English!

1188
01:37:16,979 --> 01:37:19,908
I've done my Masters. Even had a bank job.

1189
01:37:21,066 --> 01:37:22,465
How'd you land here?

1190
01:37:23,063 --> 01:37:24,701
My wife cheated on me.

1191
01:37:25,541 --> 01:37:26,542
I killed her!

1192
01:37:27,384 --> 01:37:29,151
Chopped her into pieces,

1193
01:37:29,231 --> 01:37:33,265
stuffed her in a bag
and left it on a long distance train.

1194
01:37:34,184 --> 01:37:35,186
A porter saw me,

1195
01:37:35,628 --> 01:37:37,031
and here I am.

1196
01:37:37,553 --> 01:37:40,347
-I'll skip the shave.
-Why?

1197
01:37:40,625 --> 01:37:43,425
Need a beard for my next film.

1198
01:37:43,706 --> 01:37:46,555
I'm playing Santa Claus.
He had a big beard.

1199
01:37:46,834 --> 01:37:50,230
I've to let it grow.

1200
01:37:51,872 --> 01:37:54,316
Hello! This is Sunil Dutt.

1201
01:37:55,078 --> 01:37:55,993
A moment.

1202
01:37:56,431 --> 01:37:57,632
Mr. Dutt.

1203
01:37:59,670 --> 01:38:01,314
Sir, the minister's bathing.

1204
01:38:01,752 --> 01:38:05,955
Morning, noon and evening?

1205
01:38:06,473 --> 01:38:07,673
He's always in the bath!

1206
01:38:07,753 --> 01:38:10,317
Health reasons, sir.

1207
01:38:10,717 --> 01:38:14,398
He has a fungal infection on his thigh.

1208
01:38:15,558 --> 01:38:17,317
I'll pass on your message.

1209
01:38:19,360 --> 01:38:21,245
<i>Everyone avoided Mr. Dutt.</i>

1210
01:38:21,402 --> 01:38:25,675
<i>Terror charges being stigmatic,</i>
<i>no one wanted any involvement.</i>

1211
01:38:26,920 --> 01:38:32,320
Partner, we've been roomies for 180 days.

1212
01:38:33,640 --> 01:38:36,004
That's longer than any girl
I've been with.

1213
01:38:38,008 --> 01:38:41,604
Supreme Court will hear
my bail petition today.

1214
01:38:42,682 --> 01:38:45,166
Which means I'm a free bird.

1215
01:38:49,008 --> 01:38:50,764
I'll miss you.

1216
01:38:52,008 --> 01:38:54,973
-Your bail's been rejected.
-What?

1217
01:38:55,134 --> 01:38:58,168
Bail is always tough in the Terror Act.

1218
01:38:58,690 --> 01:39:00,126
Sir...

1219
01:39:37,985 --> 01:39:40,260
Dad, what's up with my bail?

1220
01:39:40,381 --> 01:39:44,138
Don't worry, sonny.
We're going to the Supreme Court.

1221
01:39:44,460 --> 01:39:45,260
You get better.

1222
01:39:45,825 --> 01:39:48,902
Why are you lying?

1223
01:39:50,262 --> 01:39:54,268
I know my bail's rejected.
I've been in for six months.

1224
01:39:54,346 --> 01:39:57,065
You know the Prime Minister...
the President... speak to them.

1225
01:39:57,143 --> 01:40:00,865
What have I done?
Killed anyone? Fire a bullet?

1226
01:40:01,503 --> 01:40:03,310
Just kept a gun, for your protection!

1227
01:40:03,752 --> 01:40:05,108
My protection?

1228
01:40:07,065 --> 01:40:11,350
I'd rather you shot me with that gun!

1229
01:40:18,310 --> 01:40:19,470
He'll never appreciate me.

1230
01:40:21,115 --> 01:40:25,872
Praises my sisters all the time...
"Ace! Well played!"

1231
01:40:27,631 --> 01:40:29,238
I want to die.

1232
01:40:29,717 --> 01:40:30,515
Please help me.

1233
01:40:36,834 --> 01:40:38,279
There's cyanide in the tea.

1234
01:40:41,355 --> 01:40:42,236
Drink up.

1235
01:40:48,439 --> 01:40:49,678
Vodka in the tea?

1236
01:40:49,758 --> 01:40:51,996
Now chill! Don't blabber about dying.

1237
01:40:52,074 --> 01:40:53,439
Think of your dad!

1238
01:40:53,840 --> 01:40:55,886
He strives from dawn to dusk
for your bail.

1239
01:40:56,046 --> 01:40:59,680
Begs lawyers, politicians, cops...

1240
01:41:00,120 --> 01:41:03,126
Sleeps on the floor
'cause you have no bed.

1241
01:41:03,447 --> 01:41:05,603
Doesn't use the fan
'cause you don't have one.

1242
01:41:05,683 --> 01:41:09,279
People call him, "Terrorist's pop."

1243
01:41:10,242 --> 01:41:13,171
You've twisted his twins,
now spare him your suicide!

1244
01:41:13,648 --> 01:41:15,924
Fight! You'll definitely get bail.

1245
01:41:24,565 --> 01:41:25,805
Once out of prison...

1246
01:41:26,605 --> 01:41:28,489
get a sexy girlfriend.

1247
01:41:29,213 --> 01:41:32,611
I'll get you drunk and bam-bam her!

1248
01:41:33,169 --> 01:41:34,608
Then, we're even.

1249
01:41:36,450 --> 01:41:39,735
"I want to die." Enough! You're a tiger.

1250
01:41:40,331 --> 01:41:42,970
"Rorr"... come on.

1251
01:41:43,492 --> 01:41:44,852
"Rorr!"

1252
01:41:53,694 --> 01:41:55,661
<i>He spent 452 days in prison.</i>

1253
01:41:56,461 --> 01:41:58,735
<i>The Supreme Court finally</i>
<i>granted him bail.</i>

1254
01:41:59,457 --> 01:42:01,737
<i>But his name was now</i>
<i>synonymous with the word...</i>

1255
01:42:04,743 --> 01:42:07,179
<i>The public and the press hated him.</i>

1256
01:42:07,817 --> 01:42:11,381
<i>He was being tried under the Terror Act...</i>

1257
01:42:11,701 --> 01:42:13,905
<i>he feared his bail would be canceled.</i>

1258
01:42:14,701 --> 01:42:17,781
<i>His only hope was political intervention.</i>

1259
01:42:18,258 --> 01:42:22,109
<i>An influential minister in the capital</i>
<i>agreed to meet him.</i>

1260
01:42:22,507 --> 01:42:23,343
Hello, sir.

1261
01:42:24,424 --> 01:42:27,662
Come... sit.

1262
01:42:28,385 --> 01:42:29,871
How's daddy?

1263
01:42:30,509 --> 01:42:31,508
He has a fever.

1264
01:42:31,587 --> 01:42:33,304
Very good...

1265
01:42:34,663 --> 01:42:36,425
What brings you here?

1266
01:42:37,346 --> 01:42:38,633
Sir, I'll be honest.

1267
01:42:39,790 --> 01:42:40,787
I did possess a gun.

1268
01:42:41,587 --> 01:42:43,907
I should be tried under the Arms Act.

1269
01:42:44,589 --> 01:42:46,714
But they've slapped me
with the Terror Act.

1270
01:42:48,036 --> 01:42:50,831
If I was involved in the bomb blasts,

1271
01:42:51,030 --> 01:42:52,430
would I return to India?

1272
01:42:52,909 --> 01:42:55,033
I could've run away from Mauritius.

1273
01:42:55,558 --> 01:42:57,315
Taken asylum in another country.

1274
01:43:06,555 --> 01:43:08,755
-He's dozed off!
-Speak louder.

1275
01:43:11,355 --> 01:43:15,077
Sir, I got a gun because
I feared a mob attack.

1276
01:43:19,798 --> 01:43:23,480
<i>If the minister really slept</i>
<i>or play acted to avoid us</i>

1277
01:43:23,560 --> 01:43:25,398
<i>is still a mystery.</i>

1278
01:43:30,166 --> 01:43:31,207
How's daddy?

1279
01:43:32,842 --> 01:43:35,719
-He has a fever.
-Very good...

1280
01:43:37,403 --> 01:43:38,850
What brings you here?

1281
01:43:40,366 --> 01:43:43,323
Our legs brought us here...
we'll go back swimming.

1282
01:43:43,402 --> 01:43:45,765
Very good...

1283
01:43:45,965 --> 01:43:48,132
Let me know if I can help.

1284
01:43:48,691 --> 01:43:50,726
<i>It was evident, we were on our own.</i>

1285
01:43:51,487 --> 01:43:54,488
<i>I decided that until Sanju was cleared</i>
<i>of terror charges,</i>

1286
01:43:54,808 --> 01:43:58,127
<i>I'd be by his side. But the next day...</i>

1287
01:44:05,895 --> 01:44:06,891
Babu, where's Sanju?

1288
01:44:07,532 --> 01:44:08,732
In the preview theatre.

1289
01:44:19,092 --> 01:44:21,137
No one goes in. Mr. Dutt's orders.

1290
01:44:21,218 --> 01:44:27,054
Tell the Court, you knew about
the bomb blast conspiracy.

1291
01:44:29,738 --> 01:44:30,861
Kamlesh,

1292
01:44:31,182 --> 01:44:32,378
please wait outside.

1293
01:44:47,426 --> 01:44:48,386
Where are you going?

1294
01:44:49,185 --> 01:44:51,542
FBI raided my office.

1295
01:44:52,261 --> 01:44:53,220
Why?

1296
01:44:58,464 --> 01:45:00,585
What's that got to do with the FBI?

1297
01:45:01,781 --> 01:45:04,429
My company works with
the American government.

1298
01:45:04,753 --> 01:45:06,908
Now they'll investigate our association.

1299
01:45:07,506 --> 01:45:09,388
Terror charges freak them out.

1300
01:45:12,548 --> 01:45:13,513
Sorry, buddy.

1301
01:45:14,514 --> 01:45:16,189
I've put you through all this...

1302
01:45:17,749 --> 01:45:21,957
-Call me when you get there.
-No... my phone will be tapped.

1303
01:45:23,715 --> 01:45:25,991
We must disconnect for a few years.

1304
01:45:28,630 --> 01:45:31,518
Don't worry. I understand. Go...

1305
01:45:33,074 --> 01:45:35,194
Hey, Kamli. You're a tiger.

1306
01:45:43,317 --> 01:45:44,474
Let's go.

1307
01:45:54,478 --> 01:45:56,767
First time ever I lied to Sanju.

1308
01:45:56,845 --> 01:45:58,562
I can be friends with an addict.

1309
01:45:59,321 --> 01:46:04,846
Even with a guy who slept with my girl.
But with a terrorist? I'm no fool!

1310
01:46:07,363 --> 01:46:10,120
Every time I drink, I miss him...

1311
01:46:10,721 --> 01:46:12,083
yearn to call him.

1312
01:46:13,449 --> 01:46:15,248
Then I remind myself...

1313
01:46:16,126 --> 01:46:19,282
there was a truck full of RDX
at his house.

1314
01:46:19,363 --> 01:46:21,086
He's a bloody terrorist!

1315
01:46:23,132 --> 01:46:24,329
Are we done?

1316
01:46:28,045 --> 01:46:29,128
<i>Mail from Winnie.</i>

1317
01:46:29,649 --> 01:46:30,733
Where's she?

1318
01:46:31,774 --> 01:46:32,573
America.

1319
01:46:33,890 --> 01:46:35,009
She won't write the book.

1320
01:46:38,370 --> 01:46:40,896
<i>Sanjay Dutt was given 30 days</i>
<i>to surrender.</i>

1321
01:46:41,055 --> 01:46:42,332
<i>That time is over.</i>

1322
01:46:42,492 --> 01:46:46,572
<i>He's on his way to prison.</i>

1323
01:46:47,133 --> 01:46:48,060
<i>Clothes off.</i>

1324
01:46:49,019 --> 01:46:50,134
Raise your hands.

1325
01:46:52,854 --> 01:46:54,011
Turn.

1326
01:46:58,021 --> 01:46:58,976
Bend.

1327
01:47:01,456 --> 01:47:02,575
Cough.

1328
01:47:03,137 --> 01:47:04,259
Harder.

1329
01:47:42,148 --> 01:47:44,985
You dropped Sanju's story
for a book on museums?

1330
01:47:47,431 --> 01:47:50,912
-Museums don't lie.
-Nor did Sanju.

1331
01:47:51,271 --> 01:47:54,989
But a news report
became your gospel truth.

1332
01:47:57,478 --> 01:47:58,437
What's this?

1333
01:47:59,073 --> 01:48:02,230
Prison has a community radio
for prisoners' reform.

1334
01:48:02,630 --> 01:48:04,954
Sanju hosts a show.

1335
01:48:05,438 --> 01:48:07,755
He wants you to hear this episode.

1336
01:48:07,954 --> 01:48:09,434
Took great pains to smuggle it out.

1337
01:48:13,758 --> 01:48:14,922
My number.

1338
01:48:15,242 --> 01:48:17,158
You'll need it after you're done.

1339
01:48:30,962 --> 01:48:33,165
<i>Howdy, Yerwada!</i>

1340
01:48:33,245 --> 01:48:37,600
This is your buddy, Sanju!

1341
01:48:41,488 --> 01:48:45,803
Today's topic is "newspapers."

1342
01:48:46,444 --> 01:48:49,371
There were no newspapers 400 years ago.

1343
01:48:49,691 --> 01:48:51,407
News traveled word of mouth.

1344
01:48:51,486 --> 01:48:53,564
<i>Then, someone printed the first newspaper.</i>

1345
01:48:53,682 --> 01:48:56,890
<i>Soon, selling news became big business.</i>

1346
01:48:57,254 --> 01:49:03,529
Today, India has 105,437
registered publications,

1347
01:49:03,968 --> 01:49:06,977
thousands of radio stations,
TV channels and the internet.

1348
01:49:07,654 --> 01:49:10,092
And they're in a rat race...

1349
01:49:10,967 --> 01:49:13,011
fighting for readership.

1350
01:49:13,411 --> 01:49:16,575
More readers means more money from ads.

1351
01:49:17,615 --> 01:49:21,494
And how do you lure readers?
With the truth?

1352
01:49:22,818 --> 01:49:23,700
No.

1353
01:49:24,459 --> 01:49:27,215
With news that's spicy!

1354
01:49:28,251 --> 01:49:31,057
And how do you do that?

1355
01:49:31,623 --> 01:49:33,422
Easy! With a question mark.

1356
01:49:36,019 --> 01:49:41,783
When I was on bail,
these question marks were on my tail.

1357
01:49:41,865 --> 01:49:43,460
SANJU IN A BRAWL?

1358
01:49:48,222 --> 01:49:49,947
SANJU SOZZLED?

1359
01:49:52,944 --> 01:49:56,423
<i>Dad decided to fight back.</i>

1360
01:49:56,503 --> 01:49:59,108
Mr. Dutt, what a surprise!

1361
01:49:59,188 --> 01:50:01,144
How many pages does your paper have?

1362
01:50:02,026 --> 01:50:03,905
-Twenty four.
-Cut it down to eight.

1363
01:50:04,903 --> 01:50:07,791
Then you won't need
fake news to fill pages.

1364
01:50:08,427 --> 01:50:09,708
Please come.

1365
01:50:11,626 --> 01:50:16,671
If our reportage bothers you, sue us.

1366
01:50:18,232 --> 01:50:20,066
How can I fight you?

1367
01:50:20,148 --> 01:50:21,711
You have James Bond with you.

1368
01:50:22,551 --> 01:50:23,438
James Bond?

1369
01:50:23,518 --> 01:50:26,392
James Bond has a license to kill.

1370
01:50:26,673 --> 01:50:29,429
He has legal immunity.

1371
01:50:29,631 --> 01:50:32,199
Similarly, you have these question marks.

1372
01:50:32,520 --> 01:50:35,235
In Court, you'll state,
"This isn't confirmed news."

1373
01:50:35,316 --> 01:50:38,514
"Just speculation.
Don't miss the question mark."

1374
01:50:38,595 --> 01:50:40,276
"According to sources..."

1375
01:50:43,358 --> 01:50:45,475
These are your James Bond!

1376
01:50:51,040 --> 01:50:55,077
<i>Bandu Boss, I'll be there. Tell me when.</i>

1377
01:50:55,237 --> 01:50:58,207
<i>Last day of Ganesha festival.</i>

1378
01:50:58,526 --> 01:50:59,962
<i>Done.</i>

1379
01:51:02,081 --> 01:51:06,528
Your son graces events by gangsters.

1380
01:51:07,168 --> 01:51:09,965
Cops have 60 such phone taps.

1381
01:51:10,364 --> 01:51:13,722
He's not focused on work.
His last 12 films tanked.

1382
01:51:14,204 --> 01:51:19,567
His bail can be revoked.
In short, he's finished!

1383
01:51:20,122 --> 01:51:23,733
Then state that with conviction.

1384
01:51:24,813 --> 01:51:27,888
Put a full stop. Not a question mark.

1385
01:51:41,777 --> 01:51:45,651
Mr. Editor, don't write his obituary yet.

1386
01:51:45,733 --> 01:51:47,573
My son will rise again.

1387
01:51:48,172 --> 01:51:51,218
I'll prove you wrong.

1388
01:51:51,537 --> 01:51:53,616
I'm around, and so are you.

1389
01:51:53,777 --> 01:51:54,933
We'll meet again.

1390
01:52:00,337 --> 01:52:05,178
<i>A lousy editor writing me off</i>
<i>was unacceptable to dad.</i>

1391
01:52:05,737 --> 01:52:09,700
<i>He resolved to get my life back on track.</i>

1392
01:52:09,859 --> 01:52:14,058
If you hobnob with gangsters,
won't the press hound you?

1393
01:52:14,699 --> 01:52:16,066
Gangster? Who, Dad?

1394
01:52:18,420 --> 01:52:19,622
Bandu Boss.

1395
01:52:20,659 --> 01:52:22,581
Aren't you attending his event?

1396
01:52:24,308 --> 01:52:27,624
What's the option? They're dangerous.

1397
01:52:28,466 --> 01:52:29,622
Don't go.

1398
01:52:29,942 --> 01:52:32,950
They'll kill me. They shot Gulshan Kumar.

1399
01:52:33,191 --> 01:52:35,989
-Fired at Rakesh Roshan.
-Don't go, sonny.

1400
01:52:36,346 --> 01:52:39,945
If the snoopy press
ensures my safety, I won't go.

1401
01:53:00,315 --> 01:53:01,512
Why are we here, Dad?

1402
01:53:01,593 --> 01:53:04,591
When I was to marry your mom,

1403
01:53:04,793 --> 01:53:09,637
a notorious don... Mastan, got livid.

1404
01:53:10,397 --> 01:53:13,074
"Nargis is the pride
of the Muslim community."

1405
01:53:13,716 --> 01:53:16,601
"If a Hindu marries her,
we'll slaughter him."

1406
01:53:17,081 --> 01:53:19,080
I called him and said...

1407
01:53:20,198 --> 01:53:23,559
"Let's meet and talk."

1408
01:53:23,719 --> 01:53:28,322
He agreed. 1 a.m... right here.

1409
01:53:29,677 --> 01:53:32,240
-You came here alone?
-No.

1410
01:53:32,725 --> 01:53:34,566
My Master was with me.

1411
01:53:35,082 --> 01:53:37,323
-Which one?
-Sahir Ludhianvi.

1412
01:53:37,880 --> 01:53:40,762
I reached an hour earlier.

1413
01:53:41,165 --> 01:53:44,644
I let Sahir's song
play in my mind on loop.

1414
01:53:45,245 --> 01:53:50,851
When the don arrived,
I said, "I love Nargis deeply."

1415
01:53:51,650 --> 01:53:53,126
"I want to marry her."

1416
01:53:53,607 --> 01:53:55,764
"And I'll keep her happy forever."

1417
01:53:56,244 --> 01:54:00,014
"If to love someone is wrong, shoot me."

1418
01:54:00,292 --> 01:54:03,290
"If right, give me a hug."

1419
01:54:03,847 --> 01:54:05,248
On our wedding day,

1420
01:54:05,609 --> 01:54:07,735
the biggest bouquet...

1421
01:54:09,093 --> 01:54:10,133
came from Mastan!

1422
01:54:12,609 --> 01:54:15,451
-What song was it, Dad?
-Will you sing it?

1423
01:54:16,457 --> 01:54:18,373
Sing along with me.

1424
01:54:20,893 --> 01:54:24,378
<i>Vicious or vile, let no power</i>

1425
01:54:24,459 --> 01:54:26,896
<i>Ever let you cower</i>

1426
01:54:27,096 --> 01:54:30,254
-Dad, not here.
-Come on, catch the beat.

1427
01:54:31,217 --> 01:54:34,742
<i>Vicious or vile, let no power</i>

1428
01:54:34,862 --> 01:54:37,620
<i>Ever let you cower</i>

1429
01:54:38,217 --> 01:54:44,941
<i>Look evil in the eye</i>
<i>Your head held high</i>

1430
01:54:45,422 --> 01:54:51,945
<i>So what if this be your last breath?</i>

1431
01:54:52,703 --> 01:54:59,149
<i>Rejoice, you never died before your death!</i>

1432
01:55:07,912 --> 01:55:13,946
Sonny, go... let Bandu Boss have it.

1433
01:55:14,347 --> 01:55:16,114
He'll never call again.

1434
01:55:16,194 --> 01:55:19,792
<i>Break</i>

1435
01:55:19,871 --> 01:55:23,589
<i>Every shackle</i>

1436
01:55:25,597 --> 01:55:31,271
<i>Smith each into</i>

1437
01:55:32,191 --> 01:55:35,555
<i>A sword</i>

1438
01:55:36,876 --> 01:55:37,877
Stop!

1439
01:55:42,040 --> 01:55:43,200
Hey, the great Sanju!

1440
01:55:43,320 --> 01:55:45,276
Boss, look who's here.

1441
01:55:46,796 --> 01:55:48,075
The star!

1442
01:55:48,677 --> 01:55:50,361
Welcome!

1443
01:55:51,043 --> 01:55:54,400
No calendar at home?
You're ten days early!

1444
01:55:54,478 --> 01:55:58,119
Welcome... sit.

1445
01:56:01,761 --> 01:56:04,042
May I speak in private?

1446
01:56:04,121 --> 01:56:05,240
In private?

1447
01:56:05,802 --> 01:56:07,565
They're family.

1448
01:56:08,967 --> 01:56:10,403
Close your ears.

1449
01:56:12,364 --> 01:56:16,327
We reject condoms
and eject large families.

1450
01:56:17,410 --> 01:56:19,167
Now tell me.

1451
01:56:21,685 --> 01:56:23,647
I can't attend the Ganesha festival.

1452
01:56:25,813 --> 01:56:27,328
Are you sloshed?

1453
01:56:27,727 --> 01:56:29,730
I've already announced to the world.

1454
01:56:29,848 --> 01:56:31,849
My parents are joining, too.

1455
01:56:31,968 --> 01:56:34,536
I too have a father. He disapproves.

1456
01:56:37,052 --> 01:56:39,169
He approves when you meet
the gangs in Dubai?

1457
01:56:40,210 --> 01:56:42,937
Did I have a choice? I was scared.

1458
01:56:45,133 --> 01:56:47,013
You ain't scared of me?

1459
01:56:48,091 --> 01:56:50,054
Boys, show him fear.

1460
01:57:10,901 --> 01:57:13,138
Wanna see your brains?

1461
01:57:16,181 --> 01:57:19,140
Blow them out, but first... hear me out.

1462
01:57:20,702 --> 01:57:25,550
If I attend your event,
the press will print...

1463
01:57:25,827 --> 01:57:26,948
"Sanju-Gangsters Romance."

1464
01:57:27,466 --> 01:57:31,502
If I don't attend, "Gang kills Sanju."

1465
01:57:31,741 --> 01:57:33,707
Either ways, it'll make headlines.

1466
01:57:33,908 --> 01:57:37,747
But, the second headline
won't shame my dad.

1467
01:57:38,308 --> 01:57:39,864
He'll cry gallons.

1468
01:57:40,466 --> 01:57:44,033
But when he faces the world,
his head will be held high.

1469
01:57:44,670 --> 01:57:46,311
Not bowed down in shame.

1470
01:57:48,426 --> 01:57:51,795
If this makes sense... fine.

1471
01:57:54,992 --> 01:57:56,070
If not, shoot me.

1472
01:57:59,472 --> 01:58:01,556
-Boss...
-Shut up!

1473
01:58:07,515 --> 01:58:08,840
I'll leave now.

1474
01:58:09,601 --> 01:58:11,794
If I've overstepped, I'm sorry.

1475
01:58:34,726 --> 01:58:37,601
<i>Bandu Boss never called.</i>

1476
01:58:38,646 --> 01:58:40,322
<i>But he showed up!</i>

1477
01:58:46,645 --> 01:58:48,483
It's a family tradition.

1478
01:58:48,883 --> 01:58:51,086
No murders during the Ganesha fest.

1479
01:58:51,732 --> 01:58:53,607
Decided to kill you after the fest.

1480
01:58:54,045 --> 01:58:55,969
These ten days, I only thought of you.

1481
01:58:56,527 --> 01:59:00,374
You risked life to keep
your dad's head unbowed.

1482
01:59:00,773 --> 01:59:03,731
Who does such a stupid thing?

1483
01:59:03,810 --> 01:59:06,809
Head, a few degrees up or down,
what bloody difference?

1484
01:59:09,016 --> 01:59:11,291
I prayed to the Lord for you.

1485
01:59:11,653 --> 01:59:14,012
Told him, "He's one gutsy guy."

1486
01:59:14,249 --> 01:59:17,659
"Help him. Get his charges dropped."

1487
01:59:18,059 --> 01:59:20,055
The Lord said, "Bandu Boss, done!"

1488
01:59:21,134 --> 01:59:22,293
Here are the offerings.

1489
01:59:25,900 --> 01:59:27,421
Success guaranteed!

1490
01:59:27,620 --> 01:59:29,376
-Lord Ganesha...
-Glory be thine!

1491
01:59:29,498 --> 01:59:31,216
Be thine!

1492
01:59:31,935 --> 01:59:33,535
Stay in touch.

1493
01:59:33,738 --> 01:59:34,703
Let's go.

1494
01:59:40,816 --> 01:59:44,345
Get Bandu Boss teary-eyed often.

1495
01:59:44,505 --> 01:59:46,381
Free sweets will follow.

1496
01:59:47,463 --> 01:59:48,580
Sir, it's the director.

1497
01:59:52,226 --> 01:59:53,505
Yes, bro.

1498
01:59:53,585 --> 01:59:55,303
Where are you? We are ready to shoot.

1499
01:59:55,384 --> 01:59:58,584
Insane traffic on the highway.

1500
01:59:59,346 --> 02:00:01,312
A truck hit a car.

1501
02:00:03,546 --> 02:00:06,783
Hey, move that taxi.

1502
02:00:07,507 --> 02:00:08,870
Listen.

1503
02:00:09,112 --> 02:00:10,472
I've called the landline.

1504
02:00:13,829 --> 02:00:15,507
Landline's for all and sundry.

1505
02:00:15,588 --> 02:00:17,470
You're my bro, always call on my cell.

1506
02:00:17,553 --> 02:00:20,030
We missed the sunrise shot.

1507
02:00:20,431 --> 02:00:22,868
Shoot it at sunset.

1508
02:00:22,989 --> 02:00:24,870
The audience won't know shit.

1509
02:00:24,949 --> 02:00:28,073
<i>Now hang up or we'll miss the sunset.</i>

1510
02:00:29,473 --> 02:00:32,551
Time to introduce you to Master no. 2.

1511
02:00:33,794 --> 02:00:36,996
He'll teach you to respect work.

1512
02:00:37,355 --> 02:00:39,634
If you keep missing sunrise shoots,

1513
02:00:39,713 --> 02:00:42,075
the sun will set on your career.

1514
02:00:42,316 --> 02:00:45,080
Do good work and the press
will change its opinion, too.

1515
02:00:45,838 --> 02:00:47,437
Good work?

1516
02:00:47,760 --> 02:00:49,116
With such trashy scripts.

1517
02:00:50,999 --> 02:00:52,365
Here...

1518
02:00:53,404 --> 02:00:56,917
Kinky King, Rowdy Romeo...

1519
02:00:57,519 --> 02:01:00,805
Munnabhai MBBS, Punky Prince...

1520
02:01:00,887 --> 02:01:02,684
Aamir and Shah Rukh grab the best.

1521
02:01:03,043 --> 02:01:06,800
-Do you read these scripts?
-Cover to cover.

1522
02:01:06,919 --> 02:01:09,728
All read and rejected.

1523
02:01:10,168 --> 02:01:12,844
"Munnabhai MBBS." Read this one?

1524
02:01:12,964 --> 02:01:15,283
-I did.
-What's the story?

1525
02:01:17,688 --> 02:01:19,052
It's trash!

1526
02:01:20,487 --> 02:01:22,764
There's a hospital...

1527
02:01:22,884 --> 02:01:27,132
where a patient gets murdered...
every day!

1528
02:01:27,693 --> 02:01:31,407
Then kidneys are stolen.
It's a horror story.

1529
02:01:31,647 --> 02:01:33,170
I need a family film.

1530
02:01:33,448 --> 02:01:36,693
The draft I read has no murders.

1531
02:01:37,850 --> 02:01:42,851
-Why did you read it?
-I'm playing your father in this film.

1532
02:01:43,411 --> 02:01:46,773
I'll set up Master no. 2 in your car.

1533
02:01:46,854 --> 02:01:50,533
Listen to the song on loop at full volume.

1534
02:01:58,092 --> 02:02:00,900
<i>If you shirk from work</i>

1535
02:02:03,339 --> 02:02:06,257
<i>You get no perk, you jerk</i>

1536
02:02:06,336 --> 02:02:08,017
Turn it off!

1537
02:02:08,100 --> 02:02:10,864
It's Mr. Dutt's order to play this song
the whole month.

1538
02:02:10,944 --> 02:02:14,300
And check that you lip sync.

1539
02:02:20,503 --> 02:02:22,625
<i>If you shirk from work</i>

1540
02:02:22,704 --> 02:02:24,020
I am singing.

1541
02:02:25,181 --> 02:02:27,749
<i>You get no perk, you jerk</i>

1542
02:02:28,187 --> 02:02:30,663
<i>If duties you duck</i>
<i>You land up in muck</i>

1543
02:02:30,944 --> 02:02:33,505
<i>On bankruptcy's brink</i>
<i>Not a dime for a drink</i>

1544
02:02:33,666 --> 02:02:36,553
<i>Toil hard buddy</i>
<i>Listen to your daddy...</i>

1545
02:02:36,990 --> 02:02:38,866
-Lip sync fine?
-Yes.

1546
02:02:38,946 --> 02:02:41,705
Report to dad. Bloody snitch!

1547
02:02:45,233 --> 02:02:48,149
<i>Dad signed this film after a 12 year gap</i>

1548
02:02:48,311 --> 02:02:50,669
<i>just to discipline me.</i>

1549
02:02:50,790 --> 02:02:55,113
Must an ER patient fill an admit form?

1550
02:02:59,792 --> 02:03:01,677
<i>He was always punctual on the sets.</i>

1551
02:03:01,836 --> 02:03:04,032
-Has the hero arrived?
-Yes, sir.

1552
02:03:04,593 --> 02:03:07,593
<i>So I too, had to be on time.</i>

1553
02:03:10,721 --> 02:03:12,836
Shall we rehearse?

1554
02:03:18,882 --> 02:03:20,321
Just for the shot, Dad!

1555
02:03:21,559 --> 02:03:24,075
Hey, pal. No fear, I'm here.

1556
02:03:26,319 --> 02:03:30,120
You lied to me shamelessly for ten years.

1557
02:03:35,401 --> 02:03:39,601
"Now that your father's proud,
why'd you fret?"

1558
02:03:39,804 --> 02:03:43,124
That's my dialogue.
I'm playing the father.

1559
02:03:43,644 --> 02:03:45,450
But, Father...
I couldn't become a doctor."

1560
02:03:45,529 --> 02:03:46,407
Again.

1561
02:03:46,924 --> 02:03:50,321
You lied to me shamelessly for 10 years.

1562
02:03:50,842 --> 02:03:54,492
Now that your father's proud,
why'd you fret?

1563
02:03:54,650 --> 02:03:55,607
Once again?

1564
02:03:55,769 --> 02:03:59,406
<i>Prison time was easier than this.</i>

1565
02:03:59,527 --> 02:04:01,654
<i>Dad's discipline roasted me.</i>

1566
02:04:02,615 --> 02:04:06,289
<i>But, I won't ever forget</i>
<i>that "magic hug" scene.</i>

1567
02:04:06,527 --> 02:04:08,732
Your mom gets a thousand hugs.

1568
02:04:10,256 --> 02:04:12,095
Spare one for dad.

1569
02:04:17,213 --> 02:04:20,377
<i>Neither of us heard it</i>
<i>when the director called, "Cut!"</i>

1570
02:04:20,655 --> 02:04:22,495
<i>We were weeping.</i>

1571
02:04:22,855 --> 02:04:25,454
<i>It was a lifetime since we had hugged.</i>

1572
02:04:33,694 --> 02:04:35,860
...Sanjay Dutt for "Munnabhai MBBS."

1573
02:04:40,542 --> 02:04:41,536
Go on, sonny.

1574
02:04:55,066 --> 02:04:58,023
Mr. Dutt, didn't I tell you
that Sanju will be back!

1575
02:04:58,383 --> 02:05:00,546
Really? Did you?

1576
02:05:00,625 --> 02:05:01,827
Didn't I?

1577
02:05:02,910 --> 02:05:05,506
-I told... someone.
-Who?

1578
02:05:05,665 --> 02:05:07,502
Our Associate Editor.

1579
02:05:07,742 --> 02:05:10,027
Told him to print, "Sanju will be back."

1580
02:05:10,107 --> 02:05:12,350
He must've forgotten.

1581
02:05:12,590 --> 02:05:15,746
Make it tomorrow's headline...
"Sanjay Dutt is back."

1582
02:05:18,348 --> 02:05:20,434
Without a question mark.

1583
02:05:29,117 --> 02:05:30,714
Look, Munnabhai's pop!

1584
02:05:39,356 --> 02:05:40,878
<i>Look, the terrorist's pop!</i>

1585
02:05:44,758 --> 02:05:45,761
What happened, Dad?

1586
02:05:45,843 --> 02:05:50,515
It's the second time
you've made me cry with joy.

1587
02:05:51,796 --> 02:05:56,079
<i>The first time dad cried with joy</i>
<i>was in our preview theater.</i>

1588
02:05:56,439 --> 02:06:00,599
<i>That day a headline read,</i>
<i>"RDX truck at Dutt house."</i>

1589
02:06:12,167 --> 02:06:17,524
<i>Tell the judge that you knew about</i>
<i>the bomb blast conspiracy.</i>

1590
02:06:23,687 --> 02:06:28,132
<i>The first time dad cried with joy</i>
<i>was in our preview theater.</i>

1591
02:06:28,373 --> 02:06:32,412
<i>That day a headline read,</i>
<i>"RDX truck at Dutt house."</i>

1592
02:06:32,729 --> 02:06:35,249
<i>But that's another episode.</i>

1593
02:06:35,448 --> 02:06:36,654
<i>I'll save it for another day.</i>

1594
02:06:36,895 --> 02:06:39,092
<i>Let's get back to dad.</i>

1595
02:06:39,211 --> 02:06:41,529
<i>I got another chance to make dad happy.</i>

1596
02:06:43,410 --> 02:06:45,817
<i>Dad was being honored</i>
<i>at a Consulate dinner.</i>

1597
02:06:47,056 --> 02:06:49,577
You guys never praise me.

1598
02:06:49,935 --> 02:06:52,013
So, here I am as chief guest.

1599
02:06:52,213 --> 02:06:56,336
<i>Dad was unaware, his son would</i>
<i>sing his praises tonight!</i>

1600
02:06:56,416 --> 02:07:00,254
<i>I was to make the introduction speech.</i>

1601
02:07:11,743 --> 02:07:12,862
Dad, I'll be back.

1602
02:07:14,140 --> 02:07:16,139
Sir, there's a minor problem.

1603
02:07:16,340 --> 02:07:20,147
Today's headline said, "Blast suspect
to attend diplomatic event."

1604
02:07:21,028 --> 02:07:25,180
The Embassy wanted you off the guest list.

1605
02:07:25,619 --> 02:07:28,669
We said, "That would be rude."

1606
02:07:29,310 --> 02:07:32,106
"We'll seat him away from the diplomats."

1607
02:07:44,508 --> 02:07:46,595
My speech... When's that?

1608
02:08:06,674 --> 02:08:09,191
Sonny, what's the problem?

1609
02:08:10,355 --> 02:08:13,957
I'm right here. Read out your speech.

1610
02:08:16,355 --> 02:08:17,795
I wanted everyone to hear it.

1611
02:08:23,200 --> 02:08:25,876
Learn to ignore such people.

1612
02:08:26,557 --> 02:08:32,479
Time for Master no. 3.
I'll set the song in your car.

1613
02:08:33,044 --> 02:08:34,038
Anand Bakshi.

1614
02:08:34,119 --> 02:08:38,528
He'll teach you to deal with humiliation.
Okay?

1615
02:08:41,003 --> 02:08:43,279
Sanju...

1616
02:08:48,485 --> 02:08:52,283
Hey, pal. No fear, I'm here!

1617
02:08:54,005 --> 02:08:55,051
Go, sleep.

1618
02:09:00,085 --> 02:09:02,890
<i>Wish I'd read him the speech,</i>

1619
02:09:03,374 --> 02:09:05,850
<i>for... the next morning,</i>
<i>he didn't wake up.</i>

1620
02:10:14,271 --> 02:10:16,069
<i>If life had a rewind button...</i>

1621
02:10:16,748 --> 02:10:19,831
<i>I'd go back and read him the speech!</i>

1622
02:10:26,389 --> 02:10:30,717
Today, I'll try the impossible...
an attempt to thank dad.

1623
02:10:31,154 --> 02:10:34,191
In the past, I never found the words.

1624
02:10:34,271 --> 02:10:38,880
To define what dad's done for me...
every word fell short.

1625
02:10:45,678 --> 02:10:47,522
<i>...a wife dying in the hospital,</i>

1626
02:10:48,082 --> 02:10:50,277
<i>a son destroyed by drugs.</i>

1627
02:10:50,758 --> 02:10:53,037
<i>Dad fought all alone.</i>

1628
02:10:53,477 --> 02:10:55,763
He's the reason I'm alive.

1629
02:10:57,642 --> 02:11:01,238
Tried to thank him then
but couldn't find the words.

1630
02:11:01,599 --> 02:11:04,125
<i>Dad walked long peace marches…</i>

1631
02:11:04,687 --> 02:11:07,403
<i>from Hiroshima to Nagasaki...</i>
<i>Mumbai to Amritsar.</i>

1632
02:11:08,284 --> 02:11:10,842
<i>But none wore off his shoes as much as</i>

1633
02:11:11,282 --> 02:11:13,328
the jostle between courts and cops.

1634
02:11:14,086 --> 02:11:16,966
<i>Legal costs forced dad to sell his house.</i>

1635
02:11:17,124 --> 02:11:19,003
<i>Not once did he complain!</i>

1636
02:11:19,645 --> 02:11:25,169
Wanted to thank him then
but couldn't find the words.

1637
02:11:26,086 --> 02:11:30,372
Now, after a lifetime,
I've found the words.

1638
02:11:34,768 --> 02:11:38,854
You deserved a better son, Dad.

1639
02:11:39,774 --> 02:11:43,131
<i>One who'd support you... not be a burden.</i>

1640
02:11:44,047 --> 02:11:47,097
<i>One known for his honesty,</i>
<i>not his travesties.</i>

1641
02:11:47,658 --> 02:11:50,575
One more like you and less like me.

1642
02:11:56,901 --> 02:11:59,978
That son would've never loved you as much

1643
02:12:00,058 --> 02:12:02,216
as this no-good sonny does!

1644
02:12:02,737 --> 02:12:04,101
<i>I could never say it, but...</i>

1645
02:12:07,578 --> 02:12:08,936
You're my strength,

1646
02:12:09,697 --> 02:12:10,897
<i>my solace,</i>

1647
02:12:11,740 --> 02:12:13,024
my pride.

1648
02:12:13,104 --> 02:12:14,543
You're my world, Dad.

1649
02:12:19,098 --> 02:12:20,303
Love you, sonny.

1650
02:12:30,069 --> 02:12:32,425
<i>Had dad lived another year,</i>

1651
02:12:32,505 --> 02:12:35,542
<i>he'd have witnessed what he yearned for.</i>

1652
02:12:39,590 --> 02:12:42,468
...I do not find you to be a terrorist.

1653
02:12:47,432 --> 02:12:49,271
<i>I was acquitted from the Terror Act.</i>

1654
02:12:49,631 --> 02:12:53,547
<i>I got six years under the Arms Act.</i>

1655
02:12:53,869 --> 02:12:56,755
<i>The judge clearly said</i>
<i>I was not a terrorist.</i>

1656
02:12:57,393 --> 02:12:58,591
<i>But the next morning,</i>

1657
02:12:58,752 --> 02:13:02,190
<i>no headline read "Dutt not a terrorist."</i>

1658
02:13:04,357 --> 02:13:08,516
<i>All said, "Dutt gets</i>
<i>six years in the blast case."</i>

1659
02:13:11,114 --> 02:13:13,280
Till date, I'm branded a terrorist.

1660
02:13:19,155 --> 02:13:23,801
Master no. 3 was to teach me
to deal with insults.

1661
02:13:25,358 --> 02:13:29,400
But with dad's death,
that song remains a mystery.

1662
02:13:30,122 --> 02:13:34,805
If you can crack that song, do tell.

1663
02:13:35,281 --> 02:13:39,367
Until tomorrow,
Sanju says, "Adios, amigos."

1664
02:13:54,403 --> 02:13:55,929
I want to meet Sanju.

1665
02:14:15,494 --> 02:14:16,613
How are you?

1666
02:14:16,853 --> 02:14:19,251
They don't let me step out,
the rest is fine.

1667
02:14:19,371 --> 02:14:23,340
Yeah. Sticklers for rules!
Weren't letting me in, either.

1668
02:14:23,816 --> 02:14:25,734
Missing me? Boyfriend vamoosed?

1669
02:14:28,173 --> 02:14:29,617
I'm no Pinky.

1670
02:14:31,620 --> 02:14:34,219
-You met Kamli?
-Yes.

1671
02:14:34,298 --> 02:14:35,935
In your recording, you say...

1672
02:14:36,655 --> 02:14:42,059
on the day the RDX news appeared,
your dad cried with joy.

1673
02:14:42,140 --> 02:14:43,301
Yes.

1674
02:14:43,382 --> 02:14:44,738
Kamlesh has a different version.

1675
02:14:44,817 --> 02:14:47,218
When he came to the preview theater,

1676
02:14:47,664 --> 02:14:50,982
your dad was urging you
to confess in court

1677
02:14:51,143 --> 02:14:53,860
that you knew about
the bomb blasts conspiracy.

1678
02:15:00,666 --> 02:15:01,702
The moron!

1679
02:15:03,063 --> 02:15:04,106
Get Kamli here.

1680
02:15:05,430 --> 02:15:08,827
-Tell me about it.
-No. I'll tell him directly.

1681
02:15:08,909 --> 02:15:11,547
It's hard to get permission.

1682
02:15:15,391 --> 02:15:17,911
Remember this number, 88.0.

1683
02:15:18,152 --> 02:15:19,826
-What's that?
-A radio frequency.

1684
02:15:19,905 --> 02:15:22,031
There's an FM mic in our studio.

1685
02:15:22,555 --> 02:15:27,708
Park close to the prison walls
and tune in.

1686
02:15:30,755 --> 02:15:31,837
Kamlesh won't come.

1687
02:15:33,352 --> 02:15:38,235
Tell him... 6th June. He won't refuse.

1688
02:15:41,278 --> 02:15:45,195
It's his dad's birthday.
Bloody emotional blackmailer!

1689
02:15:45,715 --> 02:15:46,798
Will you come?

1690
02:16:19,963 --> 02:16:21,966
<i>Howdy, Yerwada!</i>

1691
02:16:22,085 --> 02:16:26,007
<i>This is your buddy, Sanju!</i>

1692
02:16:29,367 --> 02:16:32,214
Today's topic is "friendship."

1693
02:16:32,615 --> 02:16:34,650
My best friend was Kamli.

1694
02:16:35,532 --> 02:16:39,290
Great guy. But fell prey to drugs.

1695
02:16:40,136 --> 02:16:42,931
<i>No... not the psychotropic drugs.</i>

1696
02:16:43,332 --> 02:16:49,658
But the ones that are slid
under our doors, daily.

1697
02:16:50,454 --> 02:16:52,536
<i>We have them with our morning tea.</i>

1698
02:16:53,016 --> 02:16:56,217
Drugs called "News."

1699
02:16:57,060 --> 02:16:58,777
<i>These drugs are sold on TV too.</i>

1700
02:16:59,097 --> 02:17:03,295
Haven't you heard those
cacophonous debates

1701
02:17:03,577 --> 02:17:05,781
that numb our minds?

1702
02:17:06,502 --> 02:17:09,540
Courts take years
to just understand a case.

1703
02:17:09,741 --> 02:17:13,222
But these panelists
pass verdicts in an hour.

1704
02:17:13,822 --> 02:17:15,627
Back then, a headline said...

1705
02:17:21,060 --> 02:17:22,866
<i>It was fake news.</i>

1706
02:17:22,945 --> 02:17:26,463
No cop, no prosecutor,
no witness ever said

1707
02:17:26,543 --> 02:17:28,582
there was a truck with RDX at my house.

1708
02:17:29,181 --> 02:17:30,306
<i>So, why this headline?</i>

1709
02:17:30,625 --> 02:17:35,387
During riots, a truck with relief material
was parked at our house.

1710
02:17:37,303 --> 02:17:39,585
<i>Some jerk spread a rumor it had RDX.</i>

1711
02:17:39,667 --> 02:17:42,549
And a journo printed this spicy news.

1712
02:17:42,628 --> 02:17:45,707
Read my Supreme Court judgment.

1713
02:17:45,986 --> 02:17:48,271
I was never accused of possessing RDX!

1714
02:17:50,036 --> 02:17:54,148
But which journo bothers with facts?

1715
02:17:54,390 --> 02:17:57,154
All they want is "Breaking News!"

1716
02:17:59,674 --> 02:18:01,394
This headline worked like a drug.

1717
02:18:02,390 --> 02:18:05,114
In Kamli's head,
I morphed into a terrorist.

1718
02:18:07,280 --> 02:18:09,915
He put a full-stop to our friendship.

1719
02:18:10,913 --> 02:18:14,397
Didn't even notice
that the headline had a question mark!

1720
02:18:24,565 --> 02:18:26,719
<i>This news shattered dad.</i>

1721
02:18:27,119 --> 02:18:30,119
In desperation, he brought in a lawyer.

1722
02:18:31,442 --> 02:18:34,044
-What's this?
-Your ticket to freedom.

1723
02:18:34,321 --> 02:18:36,166
Sign and turn approver.

1724
02:18:36,244 --> 02:18:38,402
-Approver?
-Government witness.

1725
02:18:40,927 --> 02:18:45,481
Tell the Court, you knew about
the bomb blast conspiracy.

1726
02:18:47,203 --> 02:18:49,489
Kamlesh, please wait outside.

1727
02:18:53,687 --> 02:18:57,449
-I knew nothing about the bomb blasts.
-But tell the Court that you knew.

1728
02:18:57,811 --> 02:19:00,688
Tell them who got the RDX,
who made the bombs,

1729
02:19:01,088 --> 02:19:02,410
and who planted them.

1730
02:19:02,490 --> 02:19:06,253
-I know nothing!
-I'll give you the names.

1731
02:19:06,574 --> 02:19:09,650
You help the State with missing links.

1732
02:19:09,730 --> 02:19:14,412
In return, the State
will let you go scot-free.

1733
02:19:15,497 --> 02:19:18,854
-I'll be branded a terrorist.
-You're already branded.

1734
02:19:18,934 --> 02:19:21,573
It's a lie, a sign will make it the truth.

1735
02:19:22,574 --> 02:19:24,619
The country will spit on me.

1736
02:19:25,417 --> 02:19:26,814
Leave the country.

1737
02:19:27,134 --> 02:19:28,653
London, Kenya... Pick a place.

1738
02:19:29,772 --> 02:19:34,538
And dad? My sisters? Dad, heard that?

1739
02:19:34,617 --> 02:19:37,778
Don't worry about us. Leave the country.

1740
02:19:43,298 --> 02:19:46,780
Sir, I don't have a law degree.

1741
02:19:47,500 --> 02:19:49,269
In fact, I'm a college dropout.

1742
02:19:49,510 --> 02:19:52,348
But I know, this is rotten advice.

1743
02:19:52,990 --> 02:19:56,078
I brand him "Terrorist's pop"
and run away?

1744
02:19:56,676 --> 02:19:58,232
People will hate dad.

1745
02:19:58,432 --> 02:20:01,716
His life's work, respect...
All down the drain!

1746
02:20:01,800 --> 02:20:04,194
-Listen to me...
-You listen to me.

1747
02:20:04,274 --> 02:20:07,394
Get lost!
You might be a great lawyer,

1748
02:20:07,474 --> 02:20:11,036
but with a broken nose,
you'll look like a clown.

1749
02:20:17,682 --> 02:20:20,076
You're going to pay for this.

1750
02:20:34,003 --> 02:20:35,125
What happened, Dad?

1751
02:20:36,407 --> 02:20:37,757
Ace, sonny!

1752
02:20:47,294 --> 02:20:49,768
<i>For the first time,</i>
<i>my father cried with joy.</i>

1753
02:20:50,526 --> 02:20:52,132
That day, I was his hero.

1754
02:20:54,250 --> 02:20:56,848
The same day,
I turned villain for my friend.

1755
02:20:57,846 --> 02:21:01,728
Hey, Kamli. Hope you can hear me.

1756
02:21:03,210 --> 02:21:04,734
When I come out...

1757
02:21:06,450 --> 02:21:08,173
meet me once, buddy.

1758
02:21:09,892 --> 02:21:11,610
If you do, I'll be happy.

1759
02:21:13,250 --> 02:21:16,534
If you don't,
I'll live with your fond memories.

1760
02:21:19,016 --> 02:21:24,178
I'll remember, the first nude girl
my friend saw was 91.

1761
02:21:27,018 --> 02:21:30,578
I'll remember, he perked me up
with vodka-infused tea.

1762
02:21:32,698 --> 02:21:38,464
And to meet me, he bought an air-ticket
with the pennies saved for his first car.

1763
02:21:40,624 --> 02:21:43,746
Hey, Kamli. We're getting old, bro.

1764
02:21:45,982 --> 02:21:47,783
Give me one last hug.

1765
02:21:55,466 --> 02:21:59,103
Tiger, this one's for you.

1766
02:21:59,502 --> 02:22:03,700
<i>On the pathway of time,</i>
<i>At this bend</i>

1767
02:22:04,062 --> 02:22:08,108
<i>I am glad I met such a friend</i>

1768
02:22:08,706 --> 02:22:12,710
<i>Scars are healed</i>
<i>And sorrows end</i>

1769
02:22:12,788 --> 02:22:17,028
<i>Just at the thought</i>
<i>I have such a friend</i>

1770
02:22:17,110 --> 02:22:21,306
<i>On the pathway of time,</i>
<i>At this bend</i>

1771
02:22:21,548 --> 02:22:25,592
<i>I am lucky to find such a friend</i>

1772
02:23:12,849 --> 02:23:14,244
Sanju, take care.

1773
02:23:34,770 --> 02:23:36,813
Sanju! Here...

1774
02:23:37,255 --> 02:23:40,571
A picture, please!

1775
02:23:49,693 --> 02:23:50,652
<i>Sanju!</i>

1776
02:24:40,189 --> 02:24:41,108
Did you marry?

1777
02:24:42,267 --> 02:24:43,389
Opened your account?

1778
02:24:46,834 --> 02:24:49,108
Bam-bam without marriage?

1779
02:24:49,470 --> 02:24:52,990
At 80, we'll go to the holy river
to wash our sins.

1780
02:24:53,070 --> 02:24:55,717
If I don't sin, what'll I wash?
My underwear?

1781
02:24:59,152 --> 02:25:00,833
One pic, please!

1782
02:25:02,995 --> 02:25:04,718
Look here.

1783
02:25:12,481 --> 02:25:13,361
The book?

1784
02:25:15,438 --> 02:25:17,317
Master no. 3's song...

1785
02:25:19,802 --> 02:25:21,163
Named the book the same.

1786
02:25:22,203 --> 02:25:23,241
I've cracked it, too.

1787
02:25:24,839 --> 02:25:26,919
Really? Which song?

1788
02:25:26,999 --> 02:25:31,047
Hey, terrorist! Give me a bloody pic!

1789
02:25:35,282 --> 02:25:37,288
<i>Let them talk</i>

1790
02:25:37,485 --> 02:25:38,927
<i>Let them mock</i>

1791
02:25:39,409 --> 02:25:41,485
<i>The path beckons</i>

1792
02:25:41,563 --> 02:25:43,844
<i>You just walk</i>

1793
02:25:45,002 --> 02:25:45,849
Let's go, Kamli.

1794
02:25:48,888 --> 02:25:53,165
<i>Let them talk</i>

1795
02:25:53,889 --> 02:25:56,611
<i>Let them mock</i>

1796
02:25:59,209 --> 02:26:04,176
<i>The path beckons</i>

1797
02:26:04,454 --> 02:26:09,290
<i>You just walk</i>

1798
02:26:16,252 --> 02:26:17,453
Papa, what's this?

1799
02:26:19,093 --> 02:26:22,419
A story of two dads.

1800
02:26:22,978 --> 02:26:25,453
Your dad and my dad.

1801
02:26:26,373 --> 02:26:27,975
Read it someday.

1802
02:26:28,295 --> 02:26:31,421
And be like my dad, not like your dad.

1803
02:26:34,738 --> 02:26:36,941
Your son resembles your dad.

1804
02:26:37,021 --> 02:26:38,704
It's him, reincarnated.

1805
02:26:44,100 --> 02:26:45,299
Just kidding.

